title: date drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted flour and soda alternately with water beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts and dates and let mixture stand for 15 minutes.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a moderately hot oven, 400°, for about 12 to 15 minutes or until delicately browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: carolyn's easy stew beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into ungreased crock pot.
Cook for 10 hours on low or 4 hours on high.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, beating after each egg.
Add other ingredients; beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: 2-minute fudge(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend in all of dry ingredients). Put butter over top in center of dish. Microwave at High 2 minutes (some ovens may need less time, so start with 1 1/2 minutes) or until milk feels warm on bottom of dish. Stir vigorously until smooth. If all the butter has not melted in cooking, it will as mixture is stirred. Blend in nuts. Pour into wax paper lined 8 x 4 x 3-inch dish. Chill 1 hour in refrigerator or 20 to 30 minutes in freezer. Cut into squares. Makes about 36 squares.

title: crab salad
directions: Cut crab meat into smaller pieces while cooking macaroni according to directions on package.
Let macaroni cool after rinsing.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for a short time.

title: fourth of july cake
directions: Put the first 8 ingredients in bowl; mix by hand until smooth. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until cake tester comes out clean (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).
When cake is cool, slice into 2 layers and remove top layer.
Sprinkle 1/2 of each kind of berry over bottom layer.
Replace top layer.
Spread whipped topping on top.
Arrange remaining berries to look like the American flag (small rows of blueberries in a small square in upper left hand corner and strawberries in horizontal rows across the rest of the cake).

title: venison steaks with scotch sour sauce
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon butter, shallots and berries in a 2 cup glass measure.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until boiling.
Add Scotch whiskey and microwave on High 1 minute.
Stir in orange juice, lemon juice, jelly and mustard.
Microwave on High 2 minutes or until boiling.
Combine cornstarch with water.
Stir into sauce; microwave on High 1 minute or until boiling; set aside.
Preheat a microwave browning dish according to the maximum time given in manufacturer's directions. Rub remaining 1 tablespoon butter over surface.
Immediately press venison or beef onto hot surface.
When brown, turn oven. Microwave on High 2 minutes or to desired doneness.
Do not overcook.
Serve immediately with sauce.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pizza piena
directions: Sift flour; cut in
shortening.
Add
4 egg yolks and 2 egg whites, salt and pepper.
Mix well;
if dough is too firm, add a few drops of water.
Cut 2/3 of the dough for the bottom crust to fit the bottom
and
up
the
sides
of a deep 9-inch round pan with a 1-inch rim.	Roll out remaining dough for the top crust and set aside.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning. Layer the dip as follows on a large plate or platter:
refried beans on the bottom, guacamole dip, sour cream mixture, green onions, olives, tomato and top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sour cream noodle bake(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Cook meat over medium heat until it loses pink color.
Add tomato sauce, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Fold together noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and onion.
Spoon half the mixture into bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers once again.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted at 350°.

title: sweet cinnamon biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch round baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a medium bowl and mix well.
Stir in vegetable oil.
Add buttermilk and stir just until blended.
Knead the dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
Roll dough into a 15x8-inch rectangle.
Spread butter over the dough.
Combine granulated sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl and mix well.
Sprinkle over butter. Roll up the rectangle, jelly roll fashion, starting from one long side.
Pinch seam to seal.
Cut the roll into 1 1/2 inch slices. Arrange the slices, cut side up, in prepared baking pan. Bake until lightly browned (about 15-20 minutes).
Remove from oven. Pour milk over the top if desired.
Serve hot.

title: ham and potato crunch salad
directions: Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat until melted. Stir in potatoes and onion salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until potatoes are dark brown, 5 to 8 minutes; set aside. Chop artichoke hearts; place in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in reserved artichoke liquid, celery, oil, vinegar, salt and pimentos; heat until hot. Mix ham, lettuce and artichoke heart mixture in large bowl. Sprinkle with browned potatoes and cheese. Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: chicken or turkey pie
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper. Cook together, stirring until bubbly. Remove pan from heat. Stir in broth and milk. Put back on heat and boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and cook for a minute. Stir in meat and vegetables until coated with mixture. Press first crust into pie plate. Pour in meat mixture. Put second crust on top. Tuck around bottom crust. Slit top crust in the middle. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, then liquid with the soda dissolved in it.
Sift salt and flour; add to other mixture.
Drop with spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and the nutmeg.
Decorate with a raisin or nut in the center.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: honey garlic boneless lamb chops
directions: Combine marinated ingredients and pour over lamb chops.
Place in airtight container and refrigerate for 4 to 24 hours.
Remove lamb chops from marinade; reserve marinade.
Grill lamb chops for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.
Baste occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add other ingredients and chill. Better if made the day before you serve it.
Serve with Hawaiian Bread.

title: homemade ice cream(never fails)
directions: Pour into homemade ice cream maker and freeze.

title: fudge
directions: Combine
sugar	and
milk.
Boil
slowly for 5 minutes. (Microwave	is best, otherwise, stir constantly.) Break chocolate into bite size pieces.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour boiled milk mixture
over.
Stir until melted.	Add butter, nuts and vanilla. Pour into large tray.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: black bean and couscous salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse. Mix above ingredients in a small bowl. Add black beans and put aside.

title: roast venison
directions: Sprinkle 2 teaspoons salt with a dash of pepper.
Dredge with flour.
Place in an iron pan with 2 tablespoons oil.
Sear on all sides until brown.
Add a small amount of water.
Cover pan and turn heat to low.
Add a little water when it seems dry.
Cook until tender, very slowly.
Remove from pan and use the drippings for gravy.

title: shepherd's pie(one of my husband's favorites.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat the butter in a saucepan and add onions, carrots and celery.
Cook, stirring until onions are wilted.
Add the 3 tablespoons of flour and stir with wire whisk. Add tomato paste, wine, beef broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir rapidly for two minutes and let simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Set aside.

title: corn pudding(microwave)
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, melt butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook, covered, for 9 minutes or until pudding is just slightly soft in center.
Stir once.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Serves 5.

title: ice tea
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients.
Lightly sprinkle mixture with Bisquick and also coat hands.
Spread over greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 17 to 20 minutes.
Top with butter.

title: peanut butter streusel pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter and confectioners sugar; set aside. Scald 1 1/2 cups milk and salt in saucepan.
Mix together granulated sugar and flour.
Add remaining milk.
Beat egg yolks slightly, add to flour mixture.
Pour into scalded milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Put peanut butter crumb mixture in bottom of pie shell, reserving 1/4 cup for topping.
Pour in cooked filling.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs, flour, salt, soda and vanilla. Fold in apples, nuts and coconut.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 325° in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan before removing.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in casserole dish except Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle this on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden.

title: pineapple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Pour the undrained pineapple chunks into a 8 or 9 inch square pan which is at least 1 1/2 inches deep. Combine sugar, flour, and ground ginger. Stir to mix well. Sprinkle over pineapple and dot with the butter.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter well; slowly add sugar and eggs.
Add cereal. Sift flour and other dry ingredients together.
Add walnuts. Combine bananas with liquid.
Add alternately to bread batter. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use a greased and floured loaf pan or two small loaf pans.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Place in casserole dish.	Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chuck wagon western beans
directions: Saute hamburger until quite brown; drain off any excess fat. Add the beans and the other ingredients.
Stir well, taking care not to mash the beans.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart covered casserole dish.
Cook in preheat 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
(After I get the hamburger meat brown and drained, I add the chopped onion and cook together a little while to be sure it is well done.)

title: micro-easy sweet n sour chicken
directions: Place pods and water in 2-quart covered casserole.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until defrosted.
Break apart and drain. Stir in the next 5 ingredients and set aside. In a 4-cup measure, combine cornstarch, bouillon, ginger and brown sugar. Stir in soy sauce, vinegar and reserved pineapple juice.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until sauce is clear and thickened, stirring every minute.
Fold sauce into chicken mixture. Cover.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix creamed corn and eggs. Combine sugar, cornstarch, Season-All, dry mustard, onion and pepper.
Stir into corn mixture.
Add milk and butter.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour.
Stir once after 30 minutes.

title: jan's cutout cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and then chill (can do in the a.m. or day before).
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Cook 15 minutes. Stand in broth.

title: kris-kringle cutout cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and flavoring.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk-soda mixture.
Refrigerate several hours. Roll dough 1/2-inch thick on floured surface.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not bake until brown.
Dip cookie cutter in flour before cutting dough.

title: kith 'n kin cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Alternately add flour mixture with oats and water to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in sauerkraut.
Grease bottoms of two 8-inch round baking pans lined with waxed paper.
Grease again and flour.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on racks.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with tenderizer. Put in big Tupperware pan and marinate 2 days. Keep turning it over. Cook at 275° from 8:30 to 5:00 or at 250° overnight for lunch. During the last hour of cooking, cover with 1 cup of barbecue sauce.

title: gazpacho("spanish cold soup that is delicious on a hot day")
directions: Mix well; cover and refrigerate. Chill overnight and serve with croutons. Remove from the refrigerator about 30 minutes before serving.

title: mom's chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix cocoa, butter, flour, sugar, salt and egg yolks in heavy saucepan (save egg whites for meringue).
Add milk a little at a time.
Stir constantly over medium-high heat until thickened. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into two baked pie shells.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients while hot.
Serve hot or cold.

title: frosted flake balls
directions: Cook butter and marshmallows until melted.
Add peanut butter.
Stir.
Add frosted flakes.
Stir until mixed well.

title: beer hot dogs
directions: Simmer all together for 3 hours.
Keep hot.

title: boiled chili
directions: Mix hamburger with water and boil until redness is gone from meat.
Drain most of the water off.
Add other ingredients to meat and cook until dry enough to use.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash, but don't peel.
Slice in 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices and boil in slightly salted water until tender, then drain thoroughly and mash up the cooked slices.
Combine in a large bowl the sour cream, onion, soup and seasonings and mix thoroughly. Melt butter and pour over cornbread crumbs and mix well.
Make sure crumbs are well buttered.
Line the bottom of a greased baking dish with 2 cups of crumbs, then pour squash mixture over the crumbs.
Top with 2 remaining cups of crumbs and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ham 'n egg pizza
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and place on an ungreased 12 inch pizza pan.
Press onto the bottom and 1/4 inches up the side, sealing seams and perforations.
Bake at 375 degrees for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, in a bowl, beat eggs, milk and pepper.
Sprinkle ham, hash browns and cheddar cheese over crust.
Carefully pour egg mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until eggs are completely set.
Serves:

title: susie's chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add oil, then sift the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix the cocoa and water together; add to the other mixture.
Add vanilla and bake at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: luau rib sauce for barbecue
directions: Mix together all ingredients and continually baste over your spareribs while you're grilling them.

title: pepperoni pie(appetizer)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in bowl.
Grease cookie sheet. Spread sliced pepperoni onto pan, then pour on batter, then remainder of cheese (add more cheese, if wanted).
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in an approximately 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain the frozen vegetables. Place in 8 x 8 casserole. Mix them with the cheese, mayo, onion and water chestnuts. Spread Ritz crackers on top, then drizzle melted oleo over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade soup
directions: In medium skillet, cook ground beef, then drain.
In a large pan, add drained and cooked ground beef along with all ingredients but macaroni.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes, then add macaroni and cook another 15 to 30 minutes.
Will need to add water, approximately 1 large glass, while cooking.
Can reduce heat to simmer and cook to desired consistency.

title: chicken 'n broccoli dish
directions: Mix 2 cups of the cheese with the chicken, onion, broccoli, salt and pepper and put in a greased pie pan.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick for 15 seconds and pour on top.
Bake at 400° until knife comes out clean, about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: deluxe salad
directions: Gently tear lettuce leaves into bite-size chunks.
Toss ingredients together to make an evenly homogenized salad.
Pour olive oil lightly over ingredients.
Salt to taste; chill and serve at room temperature.

title: burritos
directions: Mix the green pepper, onion, chili and cheese soup in a saucepan.
Heat.
Put enough chili mixture to browned ground beef to moisten. Place meat mixture in tortilla.
Sprinkle with grated Colby cheese and roll up.
Place in baking pan. Cover with rest of chili mixture and some grated Colby cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese is soft. Serve with sauce made from tomato sauce, cumin and red pepper.

title: bully pudding
directions: Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lite orange salad
directions: Mix contents of gelatin package with lite whipped topping. Add pineapple, mandarin oranges and cottage cheese.
Mix together. Pour into 9 x 9-inch serving dish.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill several hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: butterscotch rum fudge
directions: Combine raisins and rum in a small bowl; cover and let stand 8 hours.
Combine brown sugar and next 3 ingredients in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly to soft ball stage, 238°.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallow cream and butterscotch morsels.
Add reserved raisins mixture and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spread mixture into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Store candy in an airtight container.
Yields 3 1/2 pounds.

title: dish pan cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, and salt.
Fold in oats and corn flakes (also raisins and/or nuts if desired.)

title: marinated salad
directions: Slice cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Cut onions into bite size pieces.
Slice cucumbers, carrots, radishes and celery in large bowl that has a cover to it.
Add Italian dressing.
Pour vinegar in dressing bottle and add a bottleful of vinegar.
Sprinkle plenty of sugar (may use substitute) and pepper. Let set at least overnight.
Stir and serve.
The longer it sets, the better.

title: supper corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until
crisp.
Pour off drippings and return 3 tablespoons to pan.
Add
onion and saute until light brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat
to
boil.
Reduce
heat
and simmer 15 minutes.
Crumble Bac*Os over top to serve.

title: goldia dyer's sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 14 days in brine.
Drain and wash.
Mix alum in 1 gallon of water.
Cut cucumbers in chunks.
Pour alum water over cucumbers and let stand 6 to 8 hours.
Drain.
Pour vinegar over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Drain and discard vinegar. Put a layer of cucumbers in bottom of jar, then a layer of sugar, adding spices all along.
Continue until all sugar and cucumbers have been used.
Let stand 3 days.
Put in clean jars, pouring sugar mixture over pickles and seal.
No heating of jars or sugar water is necessary.
This can be halved very well.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Dissolve jello in water and chill until slightly thickened. Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill to set.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease pan 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1 inch balls or larger.
Place about 2 inches apart on pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Saute bacon in large deep pan (Dutch oven) until crisp.
Add onions and saute 5 to 10 minutes more.
Add the flour and cook and stir 2 minutes.
Slowly add the bouillon, stirring constantly. Add the potatoes.
Cook and stir often over medium heat until potatoes are done.
Carefully stir in the sour cream and egg yolks which have been blended together.
Add parsley.
Cook 5 minutes more on low heat.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt
butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat stirring until mixture is smooth and
bubbly.
Stir	in
milk;
boil and stir 1 minute. Stir
in cheese.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over vegetables.

title: cole slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage.
Melt butter.
Pour remaining ingredients into melted butter and cook until thick.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
When cool, add 1 tablespoon mayonnaise.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix together in wooden bowl. Toss with lettuce (romaine), cut up. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: vegetable-cheese bake
directions: Place broccoli or cauliflower in a shallow baking dish.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: church salad
directions: Drain juice from fruits. Mix fruit and other ingredients with sour cream.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: diet shake 'n bake
directions: Dampen fish or chicken before shaking or dip in a slightly beaten egg white, then roll or shake meat in the dry ingredients. Bake chicken at 370° for 1 hour.
Bake fish for twenty minutes.

title: texas style potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes, add other ingredients and mix.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: extra good molasses cookies*
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in serving bowl, mix together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Make 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: country style stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove tops, seeds and membranes from peppers.
Crumble sausage into skillet; cook with onion.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in rice, 1 1/2 cups cheese and tomato.
Fill peppers with sausage mixture; top with remaining cheese.
Arrange in 9-inch square baking pan; add 1/4 cup water.
Bake 30 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broiled fillets
directions: Place fillets in a single layer in a well-greased baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and brush fillets liberally with sauce.
Reserve small amount of sauce for basting.
Broil about 4 inches from heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Baste once during broiling.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Mix together; add slices of fruit.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken in large pot and cover with water. Add all spices. Cook chicken over medium heat, covered, for approximately 2 hours. Keep adding water. Follow directions on Bisquick package for dumplings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; serve with chips or Hawaiian bread. Cut center out of round loaf and cut into 1 to 2-inch squares. Pour dip in center of bread and serve with squares around edge of plate.
Spoon onto squares to eat.

title: apricot mist
directions: Combine apricot nectar, pineapple juice and concentrate for limeade in a punch bowl; stir in ginger ale.
Make a ring with punch and add lime slices or whole strawberries (or if you prefer, add ice cubes).
Float a few lime slices and whole strawberries on top.
Makes about 50 punch cup servings.

title: beth bowen's apple-walnut cobbler
directions: Stir together 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and half the walnuts; set aside.
Pare and thinly slice the apples.
Grease an 8-inch cake pan.
Place apples on bottom of pan, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Sift together flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg with milk and melted butter; add all at once to dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth; pour over apples and sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: flan(custard with caramel sauce)
directions: Mix the condensed milk, the 3 eggs, milk and vanilla. After it is mixed, put it in a fluted flan pan or glass dish. Heat the sugar until it starts to turn brown and pour it over the milk and egg mixture. Put the dish in a larger dish of water and cook in the oven for 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: corn fremont
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° until onion and celery are done.

title: jello salad, iii
directions: Make up cherry jello with 1 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Let chill.
Use a large round mold or a rectangle dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix sour cream and instant pudding (dry) together.
Serve as a dip for fresh fruit such as grapes, sliced bananas, peaches, apples and melon.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and save liquid; flake salmon.
Combine bread crumbs and seasonings with liquid.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tartar sauce or plain.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add the other vegetables, soup and sour cream.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Line bottom of casserole with this mixture, reserving some to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.
Freezes well.

title: rice casserole
directions: Pour into casserole dish in above order. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes, covered. Stir, remove cover & bake 15 more minutes.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix together 1 1/2 cups of cake mix, flour, eggs, yeast and water; beat for 2 minutes.
In another bowl, combine the rest of cake mix and oleo; mix with fork until crumbly.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, pour in cake mix batter.
Add layer of pie filling.
Spread streusel crumbs on top. Over very top, sprinkle sugar.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line casserole dish with one pie crust.
Add chicken, frozen mixed vegetables, salt and pepper.
Mix soup and broth together; pour over vegetables.
Slice boiled eggs over soup.
Cover with other pie crust.
Pinch both crusts together so they will not leak. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: aunt helen's pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar real good and creamy.
Alternate flour and eggs, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Mix at medium speed after each flour and each egg.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes. This cake is delicious.
It doesn't need icing.

title: peach betty
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the peaches in an 8 x 8 inch baking dish.
Melt the butter and mix it evenly into the graham cracker crumbs.
Spread the buttered crumbs over the peaches.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lo-cal creamed onion soup
directions: Over medium heat, melt margarine; add onions and garlic. Saute, stirring occasionally 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle flour and stir quickly for 1 minute.
Gradually add water, sherry and broth mix, stirring to dissolve.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; stir in milk and cook until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes. Remove 1 cup from pan and in small bowl, combine sour cream.
Mix well.
Add it to the cooked mixture; heat 2 or 3 minutes.
Serves 2.
Contains 153 calories per serving and 7 g fat.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix in large bowl.

title: bernice's sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, white sugar, vanilla, eggs and 1 stick of butter.
Mix well and place in casserole dish.
For the topping, combine brown sugar, flour, coconut, pecans and 1/2 stick of butter and mix well.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Beat together until smooth and creamy.
Pour this over cake. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining sugar over warm cake.

title: sweet potato and apple rings
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a shallow casserole dish.
Cook sweet potatoes until tender or use canned sweet potatoes.
Core and peel apples.
Then slice sweet potatoes and apples.
Place slices in casserole, alternating the potatoes and apples.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the sliced layers.
Cut the margarine into small pieces and dot the layers. Add maple syrup and bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove the cover and bake for about 1 hour more.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat; salt with onion and garlic salt.
Next chop and mix together remaining ingredients.
Mix well and serve.
Makes a large amount.

title: frozen chocolate dessert
directions: Crush the wafers and spread in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Beat margarine, sugar, chocolate, vanilla and eggs until fluffy. Spread over crumbs. Top with ice cream and freeze.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons fat until clear; add salt and paprika.
Add chicken and brown slightly.
Pour enough boiling water to cover chicken; add tomato and green pepper.
Cook at a low boil 2 to 3 hours.
Mix flour and sour cream in a bowl until smooth and thick (add more flour if necessary).
Pour into chicken gravy a few minutes more.

title: lentil soup with spinach
directions: Cook and stir onions and garlic in oil over medium heat until onions are tender. Stir in water, lentils and salt.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in spinach, lemon peel and lemon juice. Simmer about 5 more minutes. Serves 4.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight. Roll into balls about the size of a small walnut.
Melt chocolate chips and parawax/paraffin.
Place wax paper on a rack.
Dip in chocolate and place on paper (I take a toothpick and put in ball and dip).

title: granny's gooey treat
directions: Melt butter in pan over medium heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add raisins and pecans.
Stir until mixed well.
Press in a greased dish and store covered in refrigerator. When cooled, slice in squares to serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: In first bowl, blend margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
In second bowl, mix milk and pudding.
Blend until thickened; add thawed Cool Whip.
Now blend bowls together by hand.
Using a flowerpot or sand bucket, put layers of crushed Oreos and pudding mixture, alternating until you get to top, ending on top with cookie crumbs.
Keep cold in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Top with silk flower.
Serve with trowel.
If taking to a picnic, put in the freezer for 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and brown sugar slowly in skillet.
Beat sugar and egg yolks until light.
Add juices and flour with the batter, yolks and sugar.
Beat egg whites.
Put pineapple slices in place with melted sugar and butter.
Pour batter over the mixture and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nibbles (snack food)
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
This snack food looks very pretty when stored in a covered glass jar.
It makes nice presents for people, especially teachers, around the holidays.

title: grilled cheese loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and butter.
Add cheese, onions, garlic salt; mix well.
Spread on both sides of each slice of bread.
Wrap loaf in a large piece of heavy duty foil.
Seal tightly.
Grill, covered over medium coals for 8 - 10 minutes turning once.
Unwrap foil; grill 5 minutes longer.
Yield 10 -12 servings.

title: zucchini
directions: Brown sausage, then saute onion and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Simmer until vegetables are almost tender, then add noodles and sausage balls.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: triple chocolate pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease
8-inch
square
baking pan. In medium bowl, combine baking
mix,
sugar and cocoa; stir in 1/2 cup milk, butter,
cup
chocolate topping and vanilla until blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips; spread evenly in prepared pan.

title: better-than-fried chicken
directions: In plastic bag combine crushed potato chips and next 4 ingredients.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise, then coat with chip mixture.

title: escalloped corn with jiffy mix
directions: Combine butter, sugar and salt with boiling water.
Stir well and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let set until foamy.
Separate 1 egg, reserving yolk.
Add egg white and 3 remaining eggs and yeast to butter and water mixture. Gradually stir in 4 cups of flour and blend well.
Add remaining flour gradually to form a soft dough.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Let rise in covered, greased bowl.
Punch down.
Divide dough into 2 or 3 parts.
Divide each part into 3 equal portions and roll each into a rope 12 to 15 inches long.
Braid these 3 ropes; tuck ends under.
Repeat with all the portions.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop fruits and nuts in a large mixing bowl.
Add flour and milk; mix well, then pack in tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: oven-fried zucchini
directions: In small bowl combine dry ingredients.
Dip zucchini in melted margarine, then into dry mixture.
Arrange in long ovenproof dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: bertha's ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions, peppers and celery.
Pour salt over them and let set for 3 hours.
Drain for half an hour.
Then add the vinegar, sugar and spices and bring mixture to a boil.
Fill clean, sterilized jars at once.
Pour hot paraffin over filled jars and seal.

title: cornflake crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease cookie sheet. In large bowl cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg, milk and orange peel. Stir in flour and baking powder. Add cereal and nuts mixing well. Drop by level tablespoon onto prepared cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Let stand 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Generously butter 9 x 13 pan.
Mix in a separate bowl the soup and sour cream.
Layer chicken pieces in pan
and top with sour cream/ soup mixture.
Crumble and spread Ritz crackers over soup mixture, then drizzle melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown
hamburger
and
onions;
add
butter
and flour. Stir well, then add the cream of chicken soup and the garlic. Cook 15 to
minutes over medium heat.
Meanwhile, cook the noodles according
to package directions;
drain.
Add noodles and sour cream to the hamburger when it has completed cooking.

title: chocolate meringue torte
directions: Grease baking sheets and dust lightly with flour.
On the floured surface, draw four circles, 7 1/2 inches in diameter.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy and doubled in volume. Gradually beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until meringue is stiff and all sugar is dissolved.
(A small bit of meringue rubbed between your fingers should feel smooth, not grainy.)

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Blend at low speed on mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Press about 2 3/4 cups into the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
To the remaining crumb mixture, add cinnamon, baking soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla and egg.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Stir in apples. Spoon evenly over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: cranberry mousse(great with thanksgiving dinner)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving all juice.
Add juice to jello in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Blend in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice and nutmeg. Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend sour cream into jello mixture.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into serving dish.
Chill until firm.

title: aunt lao's buttermilk salad
directions: Bring small can of pineapple to a boil. Add the large box of jello into pineapple and cool. Mix buttermilk, lemon juice and Cool Whip together in separate bowl. Add cooled jello mixture and stir well. Pour into mold (Tupperware works best) and chill.

title: reuben spread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with party rye or crackers. Makes about a 2-quart casserole.

title: granola bars
directions: Mix altogether.
Press in a large cookie sheet.
Score before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These bars can be wrapped individually for lunches.

title: chocolate maple nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 beaten egg. Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan..
Bake 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat condensed milk, remaining 1 egg and flavoring; stir in nuts.
Sprinkle chips over prepared crust.
Top with nut mixture; bake 25 minutes longer or until golden.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: cheese pancakes(latkahs)
directions: Add eggs to milk and cheese and beat until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until batter is thick but can be poured. Again, cook like potato pancakes; drop onto hot oil and cook until brown on both sides.
Serve with sour cream, applesauce, fruit jams or just powdered sugar.

title: homemade cereal
directions: Mix all together and toast in oven until coconut is brown. This is also good on ice cream as a topping.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows; heat until melted.
Crumble graham crackers and mix other ingredients with milk and marshmallow mixture.
Put in mold and chill for about 12 to 24 hours.

title: crab imperial
directions: Spray baking pan with Pam.
Put crabmeat in pan.
Saute peppers until soft.
Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Pour over crabmeat.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs on top and pat with butter. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces and cauliflower into flowerets.
Chop onion.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion, bacon, Miracle Whip, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Chill. Toss before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: 48-hour salad
directions: Mix well in large measuring cup.
Refrigerate, covered, with Handi-Wrap.
When ready to serve, garnish with grated cheese and Bac*Os.
This is very crunchy if all ingredients are well drained. Will keep several days if covered well.

title: black cherry congealed salad
directions: Boil jello and pineapple 10
minutes.
Cool.
Mix
in 1 can blueberry pie filling;
let jell.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish in order as listed. Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: smoky mountain corn licker
directions: The sweetest nourishment for baby is a generous amount of love.

title: apricot jello
directions: Mix apricot jello, pineapple and water and cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese.
Mix well and refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Once mixture begins to thicken, add Cool Whip, nuts and celery.
Fold all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: liver paddies
directions: Mix all together and fry like pancakes.

title: cherry spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in preserves and kirsch, if desired. Cover and refrigerate.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: peanut butter krispie bars
directions: Cook sugar and syrup over medium heat until sugar dissolves (do not boil).
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Pour mixture over Rice Krispies in a large bowl.
Spread in large pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top; then put in a warm oven just long enough to soften the chocolate chips; spread chocolate over the bars. When cool, cut into bars.
Refrigerate.
You'll love em.

title: megan's chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 main-dish servings.

title: pudding cake bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put half of the batter in pan, then a layer of topping and rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tested.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Saute pepper, onion, mushrooms and garlic powder in vegetable oil until tender.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water and tomato paste; blend well.
Bring sauce to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes uncovered.
Add cooked mostaccioli and sliced pepperoni. Blend well.
Pour in to 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: branding beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add catsup, brown sugar, wine vinegar, crumbled bacon, all beans and juice.
Simmer until hot.
Serves 10.

title: monster cookies
directions: You can adjust the recipe, making 1/2 or 1/4.

title: spaghetti-cheese loaf
directions: Combine ground beef with spaghetti.
Add egg, salt, oregano and garlic powder; stir until blended.
Press half of mixture into the bottom of an 8-inch baking dish.
Top with onion and cheese; add remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until browned. Serves 4.

title: cafe mousse
directions: Melt in double boiler the marshmallows.
Add coffee.
Mix and cool, stirring occasionally. Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip. Place into 6 small glasses. Cool in refrigerator about 3 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, milk, eggs and flavoring.
Add enough flour for stiff dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Chill dough.
(Make in morning, bake in evening.)
Bake on greased cookie sheet until golden brown.
You can put the remainder in rolls and put in freezer wrapped in waxed paper.

title: wonderful dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fill fruit.
Sprinkle with toasted pine nuts and cinnamon.

title: white chili with salsa verde
directions: Combine all salsa ingredients in medium bowl; mix well. Refrigerate 30 minutes to blend flavors.

title: cream of wheat cookies
directions: Mix fat and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: auntie letty's won bok tofu
directions: Slice won bok cabbage into about 1 1/2-inch strips.
In a large frypan, heat ginger in 1 teaspoon oil.
Add won bok.
Saute. Add water.
Steam until translucent and well cooked.
Set aside.

title: great rice
directions: In a casserole dish, add all ingredients.
Cover tightly. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add onion, carrot, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Butter casserole.
Sprinkle layer of Pepperidge Farm dressing crumbs in bottom of casserole.
Add squash mixture. Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm dressing crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: venison roast
directions: Rub roast with liberal amount of salt and red pepper.
Mix onions and garlic and stuff roast by puncturing with knife.
Use about 3/4 for stuffing.

title: kathy's tuna casserole
directions: Cook pasta as per directions.
Mix all together in a casserole dish and microwave for 6 to 8 minutes until hot.

title: stuffed mexican burgers
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Mold into an even number of patties.
Place chili, onion and cheese on half of the patties.
Place remaining patties over topped patties and mold together, making sure the sides are sealed well.
Brown thoroughly in a skillet.

While patties are browning, mix chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, water and chili powder and set aside. After patties have browned, place in large casserole dish and pour tomato mixture over the top of patties.
Cover with oil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown together hamburger, onion, celery and soy sauce.
Add soups and water.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Put chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and melted butter together.
Pat out in pan and bake 5 minutes at 325°.
Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Spread mixture on top of crust.

title: caramel corn
directions: In large roasting pan, mix corn pops and nuts; set aside.
In saucepan, combine sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Take off heat; add baking soda and stir.
Mixture will foam.
Pour mixture over corn pops and nuts; toss to mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Turn out on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: porky pines
directions: Mix meat, onion, rice, egg, salt, pepper, and bread.
Form into oblong balls and place in baking pan.
Pour the water and the soup over them and bake 1 1/2 hours with cover on.
Remove cover and brown for 15 minutes more.
Serve with a green salad.

title: hamburgers
directions: You go to McDonald's.
They make them all the time for people to eat.
Eat them at home.

title: polish hamburgers
directions: Mix meat, crackers, eggs, diced onion, salt and pepper together.
Shape into patties.
Place in frypan (I use large electric frypan) with a little oil and brown on both sides.
Put cut pieces of potatoes, carrots and onion slices on top of hamburgers in the pan.
Next, mix soup, water and about 1/2 c. red wine.
Pour over hamburgers.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.
This is a great one-dish meal with easy clean up.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and 2 teaspoons pumpkin spice until crumbly.
Press into 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add condensed milk, 2 eggs, pumpkin, 2 teaspoons pumpkin spice and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw broccoli and chop in small pieces.
Beat eggs.
Mix all other ingredients with cornbread mix.
Add eggs and broccoli and mix well.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You may grate some Cheddar cheese on top and put back in oven until melted.

title: edible play dough(club member: laine)
directions: Stir together margarine, corn syrup, salt and flavoring in large bowl. Add sugar all at once. Mix with a spoon, then use hands to knead in sugar well. Knead until well blended and smooth. Divide and work in food coloring as desired.
Wrap in plastic wrap to keep soft.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mash carrots.
Add oleo.
Beat eggs.
Mix flour and condiments.
Add eggs, milk, flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon to carrots.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken a la orange
directions: Take enough flour to coat chicken; mix with paprika and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg and coat with flour.
Brown in a frying pan.
Add orange juice, tamari and carrots.
Simmer 45 minutes to one hour, uncovered.

title: dutch
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Put in a few raisins. Cook in a frying pan with Pam.
Cook on medium heat.
Cut into small pieces, then turn over after one side is browned. Raspberries, applesauce or yogurt can be used as a topping.

title: pineapple fritters
directions: Combine in order given. Add pineapple to batter last. Drop a tablespoon at a time in hot, deep fat. Cook until golden brown. Serve with pineapple fritter sauce.

title: chicken crescent
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients.
Mix well by hand.
Divide 8 crescents into 4 rectangles (2 crescent triangles equal 1 rectangle).
Place 1/2 cup mixture in middle of rectangle, and fold 4 corners to meet in center.
Brush top with melted margarine. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
One of Brooke Bollinger's favorite finds.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter with 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.

title: microwave glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots into long thin strips.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, water, salt and cinnamon in 2-quart casserole. Microwave at High until margarine is melted, 45 seconds to 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Stir to blend.
Stir in carrots until coated.
Cover and microwave at High until carrots are tender, approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir once midway during the cooking process.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell (9-inch) and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake until firm, about 40 minutes.

title: stir-fried peas and peppers
directions: Coat a heavy skillet or wok with cooking spray; add oil and heat to medium-high for 2 minutes.
Add next 3 ingredients. Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Combine sugar, cornstarch, bouillon granules and pepper in a small bowl.
Add soy sauce and water; stir well.
Pour over vegetables. Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute or until sauce is thickened. Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: meringue shell
directions: Add lemon juice to egg whites.
Beat until it holds very stiff peaks.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition (1 tablespoon at a time).
Beat until very glossy and stiff.
Draw a 9-inch circle on brown paper.
Place paper on cookie sheet. Spread meringue over circle to a depth of 1/4-inch.
With remaining meringue form a wall around edge about 1-inch high. Bake in preheated very slow oven at 275° until meringue is lightly brown, about 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly and add favorite filling.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, peas and carrots, water, onion and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in beef stew.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sticky buns
directions: I like Riches rolls, frozen in a bag.
Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a tube pan.
Put package of rolls around the bottom.
Pour melted butter over rolls.
Sprinkle with a mixture of brown sugar, pudding and nuts.
Cover with a cloth and let stand overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert and let cool 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Cook rice according to directions.
Mix sauteed vegetables, cooked rice, broccoli and cream of mushroom soup.
Chop Velveeta in pieces and add to the mix.
Cook 10 minutes at 350°.
Stir, then continue cooking for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Pick over beans and rinse.
Place in a large bowl; add water to cover; let stand overnight; drain.
Place beans in a large kettle, and add water to cover; heat to boiling and cover.
Simmer for about 45 minutes or until skins of beans burst when you blow on several on a spoon.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Saute green peppers in the oil for 5 minutes; add onions and cook until soft, stirring frequently.
Add garlic and parsley. In a large skillet melt the butter and lightly brown ground beef; add beef mixture to onion mixture, stir in chili powder and cook 10 minutes.
Add beef mixture to beans, stir in remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove cover and continue cooking for 30 minutes.
Skim fat from top and serve.
Makes 16 servings.

title: lavender punch
directions: In covered saucepan, heat water, cinnamon and cloves to boiling.
Simmer for five minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lavender.
Cover; let stand 10 minutes.
Strain and discard particles.
Stir limeade into brew and add grape juice.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and lime slices.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and eggs, stir well.
Add mincemeat (in broken pieces), add molasses and beat well.
Add coffee (soda dissolved in coffee), add vanilla, add flour and mix well, add nuts.	Bake in loaf pans or cans that are greased and floured. Time:
1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts, pull off bone and cool.
Grind chicken in food processor.
Grind onion, celery and eggs. Pour all into bowl and add pickles, salt and pepper.
Add enough mayonnaise to make as creamy as you want.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: snowballs
directions: Spread Cool Whip on bottom and sides of cupcakes, top side down in palm of hand.
Press coconut into Cool Whip.
Place cupcakes, top side down, on serving plate.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: *May use 4 cups homogenized milk in place of the evaporated milk and water.

title: cool rise bread
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
water.
Add
milk, sugar, salt and margarine.	Stir in 2 cups of flour and beat until smooth with mixer.
Add
one cup of flour and beat with wooden spoon until smooth (about 150 strokes).
Gradually
stir
in
enough flour (2 1/2 to 3 cups) to make
a
soft
dough.
Knead
on	floured board until elastic;
let
rest
covered	with
towel
for
20 minutes. Divide in two
loaves.
Wrap
in plastic wrap.
Will rise in refrigerator in 2
to
hours.
Leave out uncovered for 10 minutes before baking at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: In large saucepan, bring the corn syrup and sugar to a boil. Add peanut butter. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and corn flakes. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Store in airtight container. Yield: 6 1/2 dozen.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Shape ingredients into 6 patties.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Spoon remaining soup with 1/2 cup water over patties and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: crunchy cabbage salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients (save chicken noodle seasoning packet for later).
Crush noodles with your hands.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 1 hour (no longer).

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cream cheese.
Add in Cool Whip.
Crumble cake into mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and smooth out.
Top with one can cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crust:
Mix the graham crackers with the melted butter.
Pat on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Mix together sausage, eggs and bread crumbs.
Using palms of hands, shape mixture into balls the size of small walnuts.
Saute until browned on all sides.
Drain.
Mix catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Pour over sausage balls and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
(If making ahead, refrigerate or freeze balls in the sauce.
To serve, reheat for 20 minutes at 350°.) Makes about 150 balls.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Spread softened Philadelphia cream cheese on the bottom of a round glass dish.
Add can of Hormel chili on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top (as much as you like).
Microwave on High for about 2 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix together and serve with fish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Batter will be a little thin.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Place graham crackers in a jelly roll pan (spray pan with Pam).
Combine butter, margarine and sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour over graham crackers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a bowl mix the first 8 ingredients well. Roll into balls about 1 1/2-inches.
Place in a large frypan and brown. Drain. Stir in the mushroom and chicken soups.
Add the onion soup mix and add the water.
Add a little Kitchen Bouquet for color, if desired.
Simmer on low heat for about 45 minutes. Serve over potatoes.

title: crock-pot punch orange cider punch
directions: Mix well.
Stir well and cover.
Cook 4 to 10 hours on low or 2 to 3 hours on high.
Makes 10 to 15 (1-cup) servings.

title: prune loaves
directions: In small saucepan, combine water and snipped prunes; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Drain reserving 1/3 cup liquid. Set aside.
Cream together sugar and shortening until fluffy; beat in egg.
Combine buttermilk and reserved prune liquid.
Stir together thoroughly all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk mixture.
Fold in cooked prunes.
Bake in two 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans (greased).
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes in pans; remove to wire racks.

title: marie's sour cream bundt cake
directions: Mix well together; bake in Bundt pan, greased well, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes and turn onto a cake platter.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Rehydrate mushrooms and fungus as directed on the package labels.
Separately cut mushrooms, fungus, pork and bamboo shoots to fine julienne.
Stir-fry pork with salt in heated oil.
Bring chicken broth to boil in pot.
Add dried peppers, mushrooms, fungus, pork and bamboo shoots.
Stir frequently.
Add soy sauce, pepper and vinegar.
Thicken with dissolved cornstarch, stirring constantly, over moderate heat.
Add bean curd.
Bring to boil. Turn off heat.
Add beaten eggs and stir.
Add sesame seed oil. Garnish with scallions.
Use additional vinegar for sourness and hot oil for hotness if desired.

title: cream cheese and olive pinwheels
directions: Mix scallions and olives into cream cheese.
Slice pockets in half so you have 2 circles.
Spread cream cheese mixture on the inside of pocket in a thin layer.
Roll up jelly roll style and secure with toothpicks.
Place on dish, covered, in the refrigerator, for 2 hours.
Remove toothpicks, slice and serve.

title: how to boil eggs
directions: Put eggs in saucepan with fitted lid.
Cover with 1 inch cold water.
Add salt and white vinegar.
Bring to boil and cook, covered, one minute.
Turn off heat and let set in water for 15 minutes.
Eggs will be easy to peel and will have no green color.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mash up and spread in greased pan the cake mix, margarine and egg.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and eggs together; spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip and spread over cooled pretzels. Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: rabbit supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat rabbit pieces with flour.
In ovenproof 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil and butter, cook rabbit, a few pieces at a time, until browned on all sides. Remove to platter as they are browned.

title: hazelnut cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
With ingredients at room temperature, mix cream cheese, sugar, flour, lemon zest, lemon juice, vanilla, eggs and half and half.
Stir in hazelnuts.
Pour into crust.

title: kristin's favorite deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl with a spoon.
Add eggs and beat well with spoon. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil water and put in poppy seeds.
Set aside for 15 to 20 minutes.
In large bowl combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs and oil.
Slowly stir in water and poppy seeds until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans equally. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: spiced apple muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and blend well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Alternately add milk and flour mixture to shortening mixture.
Fold in apple. Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.

title: tanner's popcorn balls
directions: Pop the popcorn.
Melt marshmallows, butter/margarine and jello.
Pour melted mixture over the popcorn.
Wet hands and mix well, forming about 10 balls.
Put into sandwich bags.
These are easy and great for holidays, because you can vary the colors.

title: canned okra
directions: Bring one gallon water to boil, add salt and vinegar.
Add sliced okra and bring it all back to boil.
Can okra in hot sterilized jars.
When you are ready to fry it, pour into strainer and rinse real well under cold running water; then drain and roll in flour or meal and fry.

title: granny's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Separate 5 eggs and leave the 6th one whole.
Put 5 egg yolks and 1 whole egg in dry mixture; mix well.
Keep egg whites in separate bowl for meringue.
Put mixture in boiler with milk and water; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When thick, add 3 capfuls of vanilla.
Mix well with mixer.
Let cool for a few minutes, then pour into baked pie crusts.
Beat egg whites until they peak.
Add 5 teaspoons sugar and mix well.
Top pies with meringue.
Brown in oven at 400° for 2 to 4 minutes.

title: judi's swiss cheese spread
directions: In medium bowl, mix cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours.
When ready to serve, let mixture sit at room temperature for 1/2 hour to soften.
Serve with crackers.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and drain; save 1/4 cup water.
Brown meat and onion; add tomato sauce, water, sugar and seasoning.
Combine beans and meat mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° until thoroughly heated, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan; sprinkle with nuts.
Tear bread in small pieces; place in pan.
Mix melted butter, brown sugar, pudding mix, cinnamon and milk.
Pour over pieces of bread dough.
Cover and let rise 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Flip out of pan immediately.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, take out of broth.
Cook pasta in broth.
Saute bell pepper and onion and add to cooked pasta.
Add all other ingredients, place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: smoothies(beverage)
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender at high speed.
Add orange juice slowly until desired consistency.
Pour into glasses and enjoy.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Cook the soup and milk together in microwave.
Cover the bottom of casserole dish with crushed tortilla chips, then cover the chips with the meat and onion.
Pour soup over meat.
Spread green chiles to taste and spread cheese on top.
Cook in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: ice cream
directions: Mash bananas, then add the lemon and orange juice.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour in a pan and freeze in refrigerator.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9-inch square pan, spread pie filling and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine cake mix and butter; sprinkle over pie mix.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit and rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, pineapple and raisins in a bowl.
Whiz remaining ingredients in a blender and add to rice mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
May be served hot or cold; 292 calories per 1 cup.

title: busy mother's square-pan cookies
directions: Combine the butter and the sugar and beat well.
Add the eggs, one at a time if using an electric mixer.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add alternately with the coffee or milk. Fold in the fruit and nut mixture.
Spread thin in a greased baking pan.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for about thirty minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.
Makes about thirty-two cookies.

title: potato chip cookies(aunt lucy)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll in small balls, then in sugar. Press down with fork.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt
oleo,
3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in saucepan.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into fourths.
Shake in bag with
cup
sugar
and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put into greased Bundt
pan.
Pour hot mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Cube the bread.
Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add the pineapple.
Mix together all ingredients with the bread cubes.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole(low-fat)
directions: Cook and drain broccoli as directed on package.
Combine remaining ingredients with broccoli.
Top with additional grated cheese and cracker crumbs if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chilli mac
directions: Mix flour, 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat thoroughly.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken sopa (mexican)
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1/2 inch cubes.
Fry in 3 Tbsp. olive oil.
Season with salt, pepper, white pepper, cumin and paprika to taste while frying.
Cut tortillas in half and cut pieces in half, making 4 strips of each tortillas.
Boil and incorporate both cans of soup and chicken broth in sauce pan. Cover bottom of 9 x 13 greased baking dish with 1/2 tortillas strips.
Spread 1/2 of chicken cubes over tortillas.
Spread 1/2 of salsa over chicken.
Season with above spices.
Spread 1/2 of each shredded cheese in dish.
Repeat second layer like first, except don't add cheese.
Pour soup mixture over contents of dish. Top with remainder of cheese.
I like to sprinkle some ground parsley leaves over dish for appearance.

title: dump dish dinner
directions: Use 1/2 of the ingredients and layer in order.
Do this twice. Pour the soup or broth over top and cook in a preheated oven at 400° for 1 hour.
If it starts to dry out on top, put a piece of foil on top.
Remove foil and top with bacon strips.
Let cook until bacon is crisp.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg until creamy and well blended.
Mix flour, oats, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Layer #1:
Mix together the flour, melted margarine and 1 cup of the nuts.
Spread mixture into an 8 x 12-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool to room temperature.

title: ice water
directions: Chill water until it's hard (ice).
Break into chunks and put into glass.
Fill glass with water which is chilled, but not so chilled that it, too, is hard.
Serve immediately.
Goes well with food.

title: cherry squares
directions: In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and flour. Mix in vanilla and lemon extract and blend well.
Spread batter into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Cut surface of batter into 24 squares.
Spoon 4 cherries into center of each square.
(Batter will puff up around cherries during baking.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While still warm, cut again into 24 squares.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown
and
drain
sausage.
Beat
eggs well; add bread cubes, milk,
salt
and mustard.
Add sausage and cheese last. Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Let set a few minutes before cutting.
This can be prepared at night to be baked the following morning.
Serves 8.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Cook pudding and milk until it starts to boil.
Add the cake mix to this mixture.
Pour into 9 x
13-inch pan.
Do not grease the pan.
Sprinkle morsels over the top.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square casserole dish.

In separate container, mix flour and milk well and pour over melted butter. In separate container, mix cream of chicken, Veg-All, cooked chicken well and pour over flour and milk mixture, making sure to spread evenly.
Cook at 350° in preheated oven for 35 minutes or until crust is done.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place a large (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Shake flour in bag; add tomato sauce, water, instant bouillon, salt and pepper. Mix in bag.
Add roast and mushrooms.
Peel and quarter vegetables.
Add to bag and turn gently several times to coat. Close and tie bag; make six 1/2-inch slits in top and cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
To serve, spoon gravy from bag over pot roast.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
To serve, use 1/3 cup with 1 cup boiling water.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Brown bacon in a skillet; set aside.
Then saute onion in about 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings.
Mix beans, crumbled bacon and onions together in a casserole dish.
Then spread Cheez Whiz over the top of beans.
Put in microwave 2 or 3 minutes or until Cheez Whiz is melted.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Sprinkle vegetables with salt and a pinch of turmeric and stir-fry each vegetable group individually (except peas) in 1 Tbsp. vegetable oil, adding more oil as needed between vegetables. Transfer all the veggies to a big bowl and mix in the peas.
Set aside.

title: desert stew
directions: Brown meat in oil in large saucepan.
Stir in beans, 1 cup tomatoes, 1 cup onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile bring chilies, 1 cup tomatoes and remaining onion to a boil in a small saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Divide the meat mixture evenly among the tortillas, fold envelope style and place in a lightly greased baking dish.
Top with cooked chili mixture and cheese.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Divide lettuce and remaining tomatoes among 6 large plates.
Top with tortillas.
Serves 6.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix together the Rice Chex, peanuts and raisins and set aside. Melt margarine.
Add chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Mix together and cool.
After cool, pour over first mixture and stir with a large meat fork to keep from crushing.
Powdered sugar will separate ingredients.

title: skor bar cake
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: coconut cream pies(2 pies)
directions: Beat egg yolks. Combine yolks, sugar and flour; mix together, then add milk, water, coconut and salt in medium saucepan, mixing well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and margarine. Pour into baked pie shells.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: (All vegetables should be chopped finely.)

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in baking dish.
Spread with mustard.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: hot corn dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter; add corn, picante sauce and 1/2 cup cheese. Mix together well. Then top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with corn chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, butter, egg and flavoring together well.
Sift flour with dry ingredients; blend in.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: illini bars
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and half of milk.
Spread half of mixture
in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Melt caramels and remaining milk. Add on top of first layer.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of caramel mixture.
Top with remaining cake mixture.
(Use small amounts of mixture and press them out and place on top.)
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: sequoyah stew
directions: Chop onion; grate cheese and set aside.
Brown ground beef; add onion and cook until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes or tomato sauce.
Add noodles and cover pan.
Cook on low for 10 minutes until noodles are done.
Add Cheddar cheese and cook until melted.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Beat all ingredients for 1 minute. Put in dessert glasses or prebaked pie shell. Cool for 3 hours before serving.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and flour in the top of a double boiler. Add cold water slowly.
Stir until well blended.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and clear, about 15 minutes.
Stir in well beaten egg yolks and butter.
Reheat about 2 minutes or until eggs thicken.
Remove from heat; add pineapple juice, pineapple and salt.
Fill pastry shell with cooled filling.
Cover with meringue.
Bake in slow oven.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine Jell-O, water and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade.
In 1 gallon jar, mix all ingredients.
Pour half into another gallon jar.
Fill with 1/2 gallon water.
Put in freezer 24 to 48 hours before serving.
Pour in 1 gallon punch bowl and add 1 quart ginger ale (1 quart ginger ale per gallon).

title: almond chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones and cut or tear into small pieces.
In a bowl, mix together soup, milk and mayonnaise with a wire whip.
Add chicken, rice and celery; mix well.
Put in 13 x 9-inch dish and cover with the topping.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, cornstarch and sugar to a boil until clear and thickened.
Stir well.
Add strawberry jello and pour enough mixture to cover bottom of crust.
Add fresh strawberries and pour rest of mixture over berries.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: tomato corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon and add onion.
Cook until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Then add potatoes, water, salt, and pepper.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add tomato juice and corn kernels and let simmer.
Mix milk and flour and add to other ingredients.
Let cook about 5 minutes or until thickened.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased dish and bake at 375° for 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: creamy bacon salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cheese and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain.
Cut up cheese.
In large bowl, mix together macaroni, cheese, eggs, sour cream, butter, salt and ham pieces.
Pour into baking dish (2-quart or larger).
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: 30 day cole slaw
directions: Chop vegetables and mix.
I usually put salt and celery seed over vegetables.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar and cooking oil. Pour immediately over vegetables but do not stir while hot.
Cover and refrigerate immediately.
When cool, stir every now and then. Great to make ahead for cookouts.

title: german green bean soup
directions: Snap and cut beans.
Combine beans, water, salt and pepper in large kettle.
Boil until beans are about tender.
Add potatoes. When vegetables are done, add milk, cream and butter.
Return to boiling point and serve.
Makes approximately 8 to 10 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Roll into small ball and roll in dish of sugar.
Then place on cookie sheet and press flat.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet potato scallop
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Cool and peel.
Cut into small slices. Core and pare apples.
Quarter them and slice thin.
Layer slices and apples in a casserole dish.
Make a candied sauce with butter, brown sugar, syrup and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and pour over the casserole when thickened.
Bake until the apples are soft and glaze is bubbly.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and break into large pieces.
Stir all ingredients together and cook over low heat.

title: pea bean casserole
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients to boiling, then drain off liquid. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over beans and peas. Mix, then heat until it bubbles.
Top with French's onion rings.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Melt butter and mix well with sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla (into sugar and butter).
Stir in flour, then nuts.
Spread into greased pan (8 x 8-inch) and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and season.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: date nut cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over chopped dates; add boiling water and let cool.
Cream butter, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add alternately with date mixture and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: tomato-topped asparagushouston, texas
directions: Cook slowly in pressure cooker for about two (2) hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into cubes.
Cook in salted water until firm and tender.
Drain.
Do not mash.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Mix remaining ingredients, folding in squash last. Put half of stuffing in bottom of casserole.
Add squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Cook in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 1/2 hour.

title: bonnie's baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place fish fillets in 8 to 9-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine margarine, mustard, thyme and salt. Spread mixture over fish.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve with lemon wedges or slices.

title: snow cream
directions: Combine egg and sugar; stir well with a wire whisk.
Add milk and vanilla, stirring well.
Place snow in a large bowl. Gradually add milk mixture to snow, gently stirring with a wooden spoon until blended.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: ham and cheese pockets
directions: Combine ham and cheese in a small bowl; mix well.
Roll biscuits into 4 1/2 inch circles on floured surface.
Spread center of each circle with mustard; top with 2 tablespoons ham mixture.
Fold biscuit over to enclose filling; seal edges with fork.
Place on baking sheet.
Brush with mixture of 1 egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spray 9-inch square cake pan with Pam.
Spread mixture into pan.
Sprinkle top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together with beater.
Chill prior to serving with favorite vegetables.

title: quick blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix Bisquick, water and sugar; pour over butter.
Add blueberries by dropping on top of mix.
Bake at 325° until browned.

title: vanilla ice cream
