directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and gelatin, stir and add remaining sugar and 1/2 the cream.
Heat until dissolved.
Slowly blend in egg. Cook and stir until thickened, about 1 minute.
Strain.
Chill. Add remaining cream and vanilla.
Churn in ice cream freezer.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add the remaining ingredients together and mix.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until lightly browned. Do not overbake.
Makes a large batch.

title: lucky if you get a bite
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, pecans and margarine; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, until slightly browned. Let cool.
(You may also use a graham cracker crust.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan; add sugar. Stir. Place syrup in a measuring cup and add evaporated milk to make 1 cup. Stir into saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat; stir constantly. Boil for 6 minutes. Remove from heat; add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla. Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan or dish. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Mix together all ingredients. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Freezes well.

title: fried okra pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, press into small palm size, flat cakes. Fry in 1/2 in. oil until browned serve warm.

title: vic's coconut bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix well. Add in milk and margarine; mix until blended well. Add coconut and raisins. Pour mixture evenly into loaf pan or 9-inch round pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until a knife stuck in the center comes out clean.

title: chocolate torte royale
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with a piece of heavy paper; draw an 8-inch circle in the center. Beat egg whites with salt and vinegar until soft peaks form. Blend sugar and cinnamon; gradually add to egg whites, beating until very stiff peaks form and all sugar has dissolved. Spread within circle; make bottom 1/2-inch thick and mound around edge, making it 1 3/4-inches high. Form ridges on outside with back of teaspoon. Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Turn off heat; let dry in oven (door closed) about 2 hours. Peel off paper.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Serve 2 teaspoons or more in cup of boiling water.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Lower heat and simmer until thick.
Serve over buttered biscuits or toast for a breakfast treat.

title: ham and bean casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add lima beans and ham.
Heat through.
Pour in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle crumbs around outside of top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: torta di patate(potato cake or gatteau)
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and mash.
Add warmed milk, salt, black pepper, nutmeg, chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Saute scallions and ground beef.
When almost cooked, add chopped green olives, salt, black pepper and cumin.

title: beef and barley vegetable soup(low-fat)
directions: Cook split peas until tender. Add to beef and other ingredients. Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate frosty
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender, using the on/off switch at high speed until smooth with a milkshake consistency.
Serve promptly.
Makes 1 generous drink.

title: elaine's 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well. Spoon into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with fresh fruit if desired.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix pineapple, cherry filling and coconut together. Pour into large pan, 9 x 13 x 2. Sprinkle cake mix over mixture. Cut up butter and add to cake mix. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream the butter; add powdered sugar.
Mix in flour.
Blend well with electric mixer and spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Combine soup, chestnuts, onions, sour cream and mayonnaise and mix well.
Squeeze excess water from spinach.
Mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Cut top of bread out.
Put dip inside bread.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat.

title: cider citrus sparkle punch
directions: In large pitcher or punch bowl, combine cider and lemonade concentrate.
Add ginger ale; ice, if desired.
Stir to blend. Garnish with apple or lemon slices.
Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: venison chili
directions: In large Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add venison and cook until brown.
Stir in chilies with their juice and all other ingredients except kidney beans.
Bring to boiling point. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add beans with their juice. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: meat sauce
directions: Brown onion, garlic and meat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook in slow oven at 250° for 2 1/2 hours or longer.
Freezes well.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Heat bacon grease, fry onions until lightly brown.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, bay leaves, juniper berries and 2 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Add cabbage, simmer 45 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Remove and sprinkle with flour.
Melt butter; add lemon juice and molasses.
Stir mixture into cabbage. Serve very hot.

title: wonderful brownies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add chocolate and vanilla and then flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips by hand. Grease bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until top is crusty.
Frosting optional. Sinfully delicious.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Gradually add cherry juice. Heat to boiling over direct heat, boil gently for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter, lemon juice and drained cherries.
Mix well and pour into baked pie shell.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: orange-oatmeal bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Beat together the egg, honey, oil, milk and orange juice.
Stir in the oats and let stand for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add grated orange rind if desired.
Add the baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix just until blended.
Do not overbeat. Pour the batter into a lightly oiled or wax papered 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs.
Put in greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken 'n rice(method:  foil packet)
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix together the condensed soup, milk or water and rice; set aside.
Place each chicken breast on a square of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Pour 1/4 of soup and rice over each chicken breast.
Wrap securely, using drugstore wrap method.
Bake in coals, turning once after 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Wash red potatoes (don't peel), then cut them into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer potatoes in Pyrex oblong baking dish.
Over the sliced potatoes, pour the onion/mushroom soup mix (dry).
Melt the butter and pour over the mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with rosemary.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: margy's soup cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and spices. In a separate bowl, combine baking soda and soup.
Add baking powder and spice mixture.
Add to butter mixture and stir gently. Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cream together shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Add
flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.
This cake stays moist indefinitely.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix first four ingredients; pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan (reserve 1/4 cup crumbs).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Whip cream stiff.
In a large bowl beat sugar, lemon juice, strawberries and egg whites together.
Start mixer on low, then high for 15 minutes.
Mixture gets very thick.
Fold in whipped cream until blended.
Pour over crumb crust.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs over top.
Freeze overnight.

title: rose honey
directions: Bring honey to boil in heavy saucepan.
Do not allow to boil over.
Turn off heat as soon as starts to foam.
Stir in rose petals.
Let mixture sit for 4 hours.
Bring to boil again.
Turn off heat.
Cool honey in pan.
Pour honey through strainer after cool.
Discard rose petals.
Store in covered jar.
Makes 1 cup honey.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Press in greased jelly roll sheet (10 x 15-inch).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: I sometimes just use a can of Manwich and add chili powder.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and apples in thin slices into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour fruit juice over and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees about 45 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: smith's 3 bean salad
directions: Mix vegetables listed together.
Pour mixture of the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and garlic over them and chill before serving.

title: stir-n-roll biscuits
directions: Pour oil and milk into flour.
Stir with a fork until mixture forms a ball.
Turn out on floured dough board and knead 10 times. Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter and bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: In a 9 x 11-inch glass dish, mix together the lemon jello, hot and cold water and chill until firm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla; then add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Cool and then frost.

title: yum yum cake
directions: In a saucepan, bring to boil shortening, margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar while hot.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake in jelly roll pan that is greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost cake while warm.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt until mixed the Velveeta cheese, butter or margarine and vanilla.
Combine confectioners sugar and cocoa.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts quickly.
Pour into slightly buttered pan and put in refrigerator.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with pecans.
Put frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle one package of regular butterscotch pudding over rolls.
Bring 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup oleo to boil.
Spoon over rolls.
Let stand at room temperature overnight, covered with Saran Wrap.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
In clear bowl (if you have one) pour in enough pudding to cover bottom (1/4-1/2 in.) deep.
Spread layer of cool whip over pudding.
Sprinkle cookies over cool whip.
Repeat layers until pudding is all.
With cool whip as top layer.
Top with 5 or 6 whole cookies for garnish.

title: sheri's famous fudge-filled bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, nuts, sugar, soda and salt; mix well. Add butter; mix until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened and mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining into bottom of greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan (10 x 13-inch okay).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Cut butter into flour; add pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: angels biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve dry yeast in	warm water and combine with buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir	well
and
knead,
adding
more
flour	if necessary.	Roll
out
on
floured board about 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: broccoli chowder soup(serves 4)
directions: Trim the leaves and coarse stems from the broccoli and cut the stems and florets into bite size pieces.
Meanwhile, bring the chicken broth to a boil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add the broccoli and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, or until the broccoli is crisp-tender.
Using a slotted spoon, remove the broccoli from the saucepan, chop coarsely and set aside.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Then fold the egg whites into the batter.
Grill as you would plain pancakes.

title: shrimp with wine sauce
directions: Melt butter with garlic.
Add wine, then shrimp.
Cook for 5 minutes (don't overcook).
Add parsley.
Sprinkle with celery salt.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir to mix.
Add cream as needed and vanilla.
Roll between waxed paper. Spread with peanut butter.
Roll, using bottom paper to start. Refrigerate until firm.
Slice with warm knife.

title: chocolate, chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine well the eggs, oil, milk and vanilla.
In a smaller bowl, combine well the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli (fine) in a bowl. Chop onions (fine), add raisins, onions, cheese, bacon bits and pecans.
Mix Miracle Whip, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Stir well and refrigerate overnight.

title: yummy spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic in a large, heavy skillet or saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the meat is browned.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cherry delight
directions: Pour melted oleo over graham cracker crumbs, mix well and press into a long cake pan.
Set in refrigerator and cool.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions, adding sugar and cream cheese, whipping these ingredients together.
Pour into crust and cool at least 3 to 4 hours.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: microwave shrimp thermidor
directions: Remove crust
from
bread.
Spread butter generously on bread and cut
into
1/2-inch
cubes.
In a 3-quart casserole, layer 1/2 bread,
shrimp
and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers. In a small mixing
bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over ingredients
in
casserole.
Cover and microwave at High 8 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit loop candy
directions: Break pretzels in pieces.
Mix all in large bowl.
Melt white chocolate and pour over, coating well.
Spread in thin layer on wax paper.
Break when cool.

title: sausage cheese pinwheels
directions: Roll out crescent rolls, crumble sausage over top. Top with shredded cheese. Roll up in pinwheels. Chill in refrigerator. Slice and bake as directed on roll package.

title: clam cakes
directions: Make a batter of flour, baking powder, salt, milk, clam liquor and well beaten
eggs.
Chop
clams.
Season
with salt and pepper and add to
batter.
Drop
by
tablespoon into deep fat (360° to 370°).
Fry for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: deviled eggs #2
directions: Place eggs in
saucepan.
Cover with cold water.
Place on heat and cover with
lid.
Bring
to a boil.
Burn heat low and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Drain eggs and run cold water over them and crack to cool.
Peel eggs when cool or when cool enough to handle.
Cut
lengthwise.
Remove
yolk with a fork. Add all ingredients and
mix
well.
Fill
the
white with the mixture and put egg
together with a toothpick to hold together.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill until time to pack.

title: fresh vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut carrots into matchstick-thin strips.
Thinly slice onion. Cut broccoli into 2 x 1/2-inch pieces.
In a 12-inch skillet over high heat, in hot salad oil, cook carrots, onion and broccoli, stirring quickly and frequently, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add salt, sugar and mushrooms with their liquid.
Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes longer, until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: winter vegetable soup
directions: In kettle, cook onions, garlic, carrots and celery in butter with marjoram, bay leaf, basil and salt over low heat until vegetables are softened.
Add chicken broth, tomato puree and bring to a boil.
Add spinach, peas, corn and return to boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Sprinkle with parsley.
May be made up to 3 days in advance of serving.

title: kielbasa delight
directions: In crock-pot, mix together last 4 ingredients. Add cut up kielbasa. Mix together and heat about 6 hours on low.

title: teriyaki grilled chicken
directions: Preheat grill.
In a shallow dish, combine soy sauce, sherry, oil and ginger.
Place chicken in marinade and let stand 5 minutes on each side. Grill until browned on both sides and cooked through, about 7 to 10 minutes a side.

title: b.l.t. dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients until well blended.
For best flavor, cover and chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Serve with crisp vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Melt margarine; add onions and peppers and cook until onion is soft.
Add flour and stir in.
Add chicken stock and cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Quarter cucumbers lengthwise; scoop out seeds and cut crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until cucumbers are tender.
Blend until smooth before serving.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle on Parmesan. Bake for additional 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm milk.
Add shortening and half the flour.
Beat until perfectly smooth.
Add salt and remainder of flour.
Knead well and place in greased bowl.
Cover. Let rise until double in bulk.
Stir down.
Cover well and place in refrigerator until needed.
To use, cut off as much dough as desired; roll out on lightly floured board.
Shape into rolls and place in greased pans.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Make 3 holes: hole No. 1 - oil; hole No. 2 - vinegar; hole No. 3 - vanilla. Pour water over all and mix well. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes. You can mix this right in the 13 x 9 pan.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Just mix together all ingredients except jam and pie filling. Put in two pans.
Put jam between layers after cake has cooled. Put layers together and cover with Cool Whip.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy noodles for one
directions: Boil egg noodles 10 to 15 minutes or until soft.
Drain.
Heat margarine in a pan with chopped onion until transparent.
Add the noodles and cheese; continue to cook until the cheese has melted.

title: garlic and parsley potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; toss to coat well.
Layer half of potato mixture in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle half of parsley over potatoes. Layer remaining potato mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tender.
Uncover and sprinkle remaining parsley over potatoes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: angel delight cake
directions: Tear cake into bite-sized pieces.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in strawberries and sugar.
Chill until thickened; fold in whipped cream.
Place half the cake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Add half the strawberry mixture.
Repeat layers; refrigerate until firm.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough flour to make thick dough. Bake in moderate 350° oven until lightly brown.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Fold in onion, squash and carrots.
Combine stuffing mix with butter or margarine.
Spread half of mix in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetable mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake at 450° for 45 minutes, then 15 minutes at 350°.

title: trash
directions: You will need 1 small white trash bag and tie.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Meat Loaf:
Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onions, half of tomato sauce, eggs, salt, pepper and water.

title: vichyssoise or leek-potato soup
directions: Mince leeks and onion and saute in butter for 3 minutes.
Add potatoes and chicken broth.
Simmer, covered, for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Put vegetables through food mill or blender. Return puree to broth.
Remove from heat.
Add cream; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot or cold.
Top with chopped fresh chives.

title: pineapple-cheese combination
directions: Add pineapple juice alternately with sugar-flour combination. Cook until thick.
Put layer of pineapple chunks and layer of grated cheese in small casserole and pour sauce over this. Repeat.
Let chill before serving.

title: appetizer sauce
directions: Combine and heat on low heat. Serve over meatballs, kielbasa or smoky links.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Mix first four ingredients and boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Add vanilla after boiling.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows in top of a double boiler.
Add the Hershey bar and mix until melted and blended.
Cool.
Fold the chocolate mixture into the whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes. Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: fruit and angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Arrange half of the cake pieces in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the undrained pineapple and cherries.
Spread half of the dessert topping over all and top with half of the coconut.
Repeat layers, ending with dessert topping and coconut.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain off fat.
Add kidney beans, salt, chili powder and garlic powder.
Add the Catalina and simmer about 10 minutes.
Let cool.
In large bowl combine the lettuce, diced tomatoes, onions and Cheddar cheese. Add the meat mixture and crushed Doritos.
Toss and serve.

title: pizza pockets
directions: In bowl combine tomato sauce, oregano, basil and garlic; stir. Add Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Add peppers, if desired.
Set aside.

title: make ahead slaw
directions: Bring to a boil and let cool.
Soak 1 quart shredded cabbage, 1/2 green pepper and some shredded carrots for color in 2 cups cold water with 1 teaspoon of salt for 2 hours.
Drain.
Add 3 celery stalks.
Cut fine.
Then pour vinegar mixture over it. Keep in refrigerator.

title: suet pudding
directions: Stir; pour into tube pan and steam 2 1/2 hours.
Cool thoroughly.
May be frozen and kept several days.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix and bake 20 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Combine 2 cups tomato juice, onion, celery leaves, sugar, salt, bay leaves and cloves.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes; strain.

title: tea muffins
directions: Stir flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together, then add bran flakes.
Beat egg and add water, Sweet 'N Low and salad oil. Stir into dry ingredients, mixing as little as possible.
Add raisins.
Line muffin pans with paper liners and divide batter evenly in 12 muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese baked chicken
directions: Mix cheese, onion, garlic powder, salt, basil, oregano and pepper.
Roll chicken pieces in the mixture to coat well.
Place in large casserole.
Cover tightly.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 1/2 hours, until chicken is tender and lightly browned. Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 servings, 290 calories each.

title: hot cakes
directions: Add flour to thicken, not too thick, a little sugar (about 1 tablespoon) and 2 teaspoons butter.
I make mine about the size of a silver dollar.

title: old fashioned biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits in pan.
Mix eggs, vanilla, sugar and milk together.
Stir into biscuits.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter together and press into flat pan.
Add coconut, then nuts, then chocolate chips.
Pour 1 can sweetened condensed milk over top of layers.
Bake in oven at 350° for thirty-five minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients, spoon into pie shell and freeze. Serve frozen, topped with chocolate curls.

title: chocolate chip and nut cake
directions: In an 8-inch pan, stir cake mix, egg, milk and vanilla with rubber spatula until well blended.
Scrape down sides of pan. Sprinkle evenly with chocolate pieces and nuts.
This has 258 calories.
Bake according to Snack-Cake directions.

title: potato pancakes(placki kartoflane)
directions: Using grater blade of food processor, grate potatoes and onion.
Combine with salt, eggs and flour (a bit more if needed). Spoon batter with large soup spoon into hot lard and fry until golden brown on each side.
Serve immediately.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add pineapple.
Add flour, soda, vanilla and pecans.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: makes its own crust coconut custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Grease a glass pie plate very well.
You must use a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple mold
directions: Dissolve raspberry-flavored gelatin in boiling water and let cool.
Stir in next 7 ingredients and spoon into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain water (press).
Mix all ingredients well.
Chill overnight.
Makes a great spread with crackers and vegetables.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel, then let soak in cold water for several hours the potatoes.
Drain them well; dry, then grate them coarsely.
Drain them.
There should be 2 cupfuls.
Place them in a bowl.
Beat well, then stir in the eggs.
Combine and sift, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the flour to the potato mixture with onion. Saute by spoonfuls in 1/4-inch or more of hot fat.
Turn and brown the second side.
These are usually served with sour cream or applesauce.

title: apple crisp(6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes, until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm and, if desired, with light cream or ice cream.

title: caramel candy
directions: Put sugar, cream and syrup in a large saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff and pour in buttered platter.
Slice.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: In 4-quart saucepan or wok, heat water to boiling.
Add walnuts and boil 1 minute.
Rinse under hot water and drain.

title: effie's homemade pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix
everything for custard except pineapple and juice. Set pot
in
pan
of water and cook custard (about 45 minutes) until custard
coats
the spoon, then add pineapple and lemon juice. Cool
mixture
before
freezing.
Freeze
for about 30 minutes.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Boil and cool the sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper and salt. Drain remaining ingredients.
Mix and let stand overnight before serving.

title: pizza made easy
directions: Preheat oven according to biscuit directions.
Separate refrigerated biscuits.
Press biscuits flat in middle making a rim around the outside edge.
Spread pizza sauce on biscuit.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Top with 3 pepperoni.
Bake according to package directions.
Serve.

title: chip and dip chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare chicken; wash and pat dry. Coat each chicken piece with onion dip, then roll in potato chips. Place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix self-rising flour, margarine and nuts together.
Spread in bottom of a slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan or ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cherry slush
directions: Combine the boiling water and sugar.
Add tea bags.
Let steep for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags; discard.
Cool sugar mixture.
Add vodka and orange juice.

title: italian green beans with onion and basil
directions: Saute onion in oil and butter for 5 minutes or until tender. Add beans and remaining ingredients and cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until beans are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Use 1/2 of the angel food cake to layer the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Slice the ice cream and layer on top of cake. Repeat layering.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad(the late vera mckinney's)
directions: Add marshmallows to lemon jello.
Stir until melted.
Let mixture cool, not set up.
Add pineapple and juice.
Then add cottage cheese and nuts.
Stir up.
Put in refrigerator.
Watch closely.
In about 20 minutes, after it starts congealing, add whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 10 small or 9 individual servings or an 8-inch mold.

title: green pasta with bacon sauce
directions: Fry bacon. Cut in pieces and add the garlic (if the juice of the bacon is too much, pour out). Add the crushed tomatoes and simmer. Add salt and pepper. Boil pasta; mix with sauce. Add grated Parmesan cheese.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in bowl.
Blend 1/3 cup vegetable oil.
Add boiling water.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: apple pie with walnut topping
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Combine sugar and next 4 ingredients.
Add to apple mixture. Spoon into 9-inch pastry crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Then sprinkle with walnut topping.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can serve with ice cream.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter. Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill for 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple; reserve liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add enough cold water to reserved blueberry and pineapple liquid equal to 1 3/4 cups.
Add to gelatin.
When gelatin is slightly thickened, fold in fruit.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish and chill until firm.
In a separate dish, combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over gelatin; top with pecans and chill.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly. Save 1 cup; pat remainder lightly into an ungreased 13x9 inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth. Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Bake 15 minutes longer. Cool; cut into bars.

title: broccoli-tomato casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in unsalted boiling water for 5 to 7 minutes or until broccoli is tender; drain.
Combine eggs, soup and oregano. Stir in tomatoes and cooked broccoli.
Turn the vegetable-cheese mixture into a 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Use for strawberries, raspberries, etc.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour; beat well and then add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into an 8 x 11 1/2-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Pour fruit on top of butter.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder and pour on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until batter raises and is golden brown.

title: mom's best bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Butter a square baking dish.
Cover with torn bread pieces.
Beat eggs and mix with milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour over bread and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in a pan of hot water and bake one hour or until brown.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Mix well and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: In bottom of dish, layer bean dip.
Next mix taco mix and spread on bean dip.
Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream, then layer lettuce, tomatoes, onions, cheese and olives.
Mash down and refrigerate a few hours.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients, except strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat strawberries with electric mixer and stir in thoroughly with other ingredients. Pour into two 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes and remove (I use 4 small loaf pans).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar for at least 10 minutes.
Beat in egg yolks,
one
at
a time.
Beat in flour and soda (which have been mixed) alternately with sour cream.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract.
Fold
in	beaten	egg
whites.
Pour into well-greased and
lightly
floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven
for
1/2 hours for tube pan and 1 hour and 45 minutes for Bundt.	(Bundt will rise above edge of pan and form thick crust if pan has been heavily greased.)

title: red and white strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin with hot water.
Add partially thawed strawberries. Stir well, then add bananas and pineapple.
Place half of mixture in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put into refrigerator.
Allow the other half to thicken slightly, but remain at pouring consistency.
When refrigerated half is set, top with sour cream.
Add remaining fruit mixture and return to refrigerator.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: rice with lemon
directions: Bring water to boil in large saucepan.
Meanwhile, in bowl or pitcher with pouring spout, combine rice and salt.
Over high heat, pour rice into boiling water in slow, steady stream so as not to break boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer uncovered until rice is cooked 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: traditional easter sweet cheese
directions: Place a gallon of thickened sour milk on the stove.
Stir constantly and heat (about 102°) until you can press curds of milk together with the hand.
Pour the milk into cheesecloth and thoroughly press out the whey.
Put 2 tablespoons butter in a hot skillet.
Melt, then add the curds, 1 tablespoons soda and salt (approximately 1 teaspoon or according to taste).
Stir with a potato masher. Cook until smooth, then add cream or milk to thickness desired.
Pour into a bowl and it is ready to serve.

title: egg noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Set aside. Saute celery, pepper and onion in the margarine a few minutes; add salt. Mix soup with milk, add the vegetable mix; add ham, mushrooms and olives. Add all to noodles and put into a baking dish. Sprinkle some sliced almonds on top and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: quills with spicy tomato and bacon sauce
directions: Remove the cores from tomatoes and score an "x" on the base of each.
Immerse in a pan of boiling water until the skin starts to split, 8 to 15 seconds.
Transfer to cold water.
When cold, peel off skins.
Cut tomatoes crosswise in half; squeeze out the seeds, then coarsely chop each half.
Wearing rubber gloves, dice the chili pepper.
Finely chop the garlic.
Wipe the mushrooms with damp paper towels; trim stems even with caps.
Slice them.
Strip oregano leaves from stems, reserving leaves for garnish.
Chop leaves.
Stack bacon slices and cut across in wide strips. Transfer bacon to frying pan.
Fry over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the bacon is lightly browned and fat is melted, 5 to 7 minutes.
Spoon off most of the fat, leaving about 3 tablespoons to saute mushrooms in.
Increase heat and add mushrooms.
Cook until mushrooms have softened and most liquid has evaporated, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add garlic, chili pepper, oregano, chopped tomatoes with any juice, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover with a lid and simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thick and rich, 25 to 30 minutes.
Taste for seasoning. Fill large pot with cold water; bring to a boil and add 1 tablespoon salt.
Then add the quills.
Simmer until tender, but still chewy, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain quills and rinse in hot water.
Drain again.
Transfer quills to a warmed serving bowl and add butter.
Toss with 2 forks until well coated. Spoon over the sauce and half of the grated cheese.
Toss together, then sprinkle over a little more cheese and garnish with reserved oregano leaves.
Serve immediately with the remaining cheese.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, jello and sugar. Add water and food coloring.
Cook until thick. Cool.
Add strawberries and pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate until cold. Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Spread	margarine on bread.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over bread.
Toast in oven until lightly browned.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni or pasta of choice until tender.
Rinse and drain.
Toss with other ingredients and mix with cole slaw dressing.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve with hot milk.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: jon ben getty
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Cook noodles in salted water. Cook green peas as directed.
Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and small amount of cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: florida grapefruit salad
directions: Arrange salad greens in serving bowl.
Place chunks of crabmeat in middle.
Surround with grapefruit sections.
Serve with Grapefruit Dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine in a large skillet, flour, cocoa, sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add butter.
Let boil until thickened.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups with cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In large bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, beat egg whites lightly.
Stir in mashed bananas, milk and corn syrup.
Add flour mixture; stir until well blended.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove; cool on wire rack.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until tender, but not well done.
Separate buds and dip in egg.
Roll in meal or crumbs. Brown in hot oil, turning to brown all over.
Serve hot, sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: layered ole dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.

title: drop donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given.
Drop from tablespoon into hot grease (350°).
Fry until brown, then turn.

title: salt-free blend
directions: Combine and mix well.
Spoon into shaker.

title: granny apple snicker salad
directions: Cut unpeeled apples in half inch pieces.
Cut candy bars in small pieces.
Whip cream cheese until soft.
Add whipped topping and apples and candy bar pieces.

title: pineapple layer cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to directions. Beat in oranges until blended. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool for ten minutes before removing from pans. Remove from pans and cool completely. Combine pineapple and dry pudding mix, fold in whipped topping. Spread between layers, over top and sides. Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Rinse wings and pat dry.
Cut apart; discard tip.
Arrange in one layer on large cookie sheet lined with foil.
Mix soy sauce and oil; brush over wings.
Mix brown sugar, salt and chili powder.
Sprinkle evenly over top of wings.
Place under broiler until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Mix soup and vinegar. Pour over wings.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.

title: lemon-orange butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Cover and chill if not ready to use.
Let butter soften before serving.
Makes 1/4 cup.

title: lemon coconut frosting
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup water and set aside.
Bring 1 cup water to a boil; stir in sugar, lemon rind and lemon juice. Return to boil and cook 7 minutes, until candy thermometer reaches soft ball stage.
Gradually stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in coconut.
Cool.
Stir frosting just before spreading on cake.
Will cover 1 three layer cake.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Brown the beef, adding pepper and salt.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil, then simmer for 45 minutes.
Add Tabasco sauce if desired.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, lemon juice, chives and a dash of pepper.
Beat well.
Stir in cheese and bacon.
Chill.
Roll 1 of the patty shells in an 8 x 4-inch rectangle.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Top each square with a rounded teaspoonful of filling. Brush edges with milk.
Fold to form triangles.
Seal.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining shells and filling.
Chill appetizers until ready to bake.
Place in 450° oven.
Immediately reduce temperature to 400°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 32.
A good "make ahead."
Warm before serving.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
When brown add 2 tablespoons flour over meat and fry until crumbly.
Then add the last 5 ingredients; cover and cook 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, place chopped cabbage, pineapple, apple, raisins, marshmallows, bananas and all but 1 tablespoon chopped walnuts.
Mix together.

title: great potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add milk and stir and cook until thick.
Pour over potatoes.
Great side dish.

title: virginia diner peanut pie
directions: *Peanuts should be placed in a white ham wrapper bag and beaten with a wooden mallet. This enhances the flavor.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Split zucchini long way, throw seeds away, then scoop out meaty inside with grapefruit spoon.
Cook this with ground meat and chopped onions.
Add other ingredients except tomato sauce and cheese.

title: carrot relish
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, tomato soup, vegetable oil, salt and pepper together.
When slightly cool, pour over carrots, onion and green pepper.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 days.

title: dillards jello salad
directions: Make gelatin with water and ice.
Blend together topping and sour cream.
Add gelatin to creamy mix, blending with wire whisk. Yields 1 quart.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apricot jello
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Put in deep bowl; mix with spoon.
Dissolve
the Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup water; add to first mixture.
Add
the	whipping
cream.
Mix
all at low speed for 2 minutes.
Put
in
a 9 x 13-inch pan; refrigerate after cooling.

title: rice and coconut pudding
directions: Mix well together cooked rice, coconut, raisins, sugar and salt.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Beat eggs lightly. Combine with milk and vanilla.
Pour over rice mixture and sprinkle with grated orange peel over top.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to mixture all at once.
Stir until mixed but sticky.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead gently about 15 strokes.
Roll to 3/4 inch thickness, cut with glass dipped in flour.
Put on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Stir flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture to sweet potatoes alternately with milk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Yields 2 to 3 dozen muffins.
Excellent compliment with a country ham dinner!

title: lemon-blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Make a well in center of flour.
Combine milk, egg and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients; stir quickly, just until all ingredients are moistened.
Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons sugar; gently stir into batter, along with lemon peel. Fill 2 1/2-inch muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
While muffins are still warm, dip tops in melted butter, then in a little sugar.

title: peanut butter creme pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with peanut butter until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and mix well (will be stiff).
Add Cool Whip, mix well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill before serving.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, salad dressing, cocoa, warm water and soda; add flour, salt and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes. Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 2 layer cake pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 8 slices bread on one side; put butter side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put ham and cheese on bread.
Layer with remainder of bread.
Pour beaten eggs on top of bread.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be made night before.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk until soft ball forms in cold water.
Add margarine, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat the ingredients until you get a good spreading consistency.
Spread on greased cookie sheet or platter.
Fudge can be cut and served or can be refrigerated.

title: orange-pineapple dessert(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all and put in 2 graham cracker crusts; chill.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine salt, sugar, oil and cold water.
Add yeast and egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add 2 2/3 cups flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover. Let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down.
Place in refrigerator or make into rolls.
Will keep 3 or 4 days in fridge. Bake at 400°.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Make 2 rolls; wrap in foil.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Open foil and bake 15 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and milk; stir well.
Spoon sauce over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Combine with sifted dry ingredients.
Drop on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Have a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish ready.
Coat a nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook eggplant (in batches) over medium heat 4 minutes per side or until golden and tender. Mix spinach, Ricotta and cottage cheeses, 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese and the eggs until blended.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Place 3 noodles lengthwise on top.
Cover with half the spinach mixture, then half the eggplant and 5 slices Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat for second layer.
Top with remaining noodles, overlapping to cover, then remaining sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Bake 1 hour or until bubbling and lightly brown around edges.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting in 12 pieces.
Serves 12.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the pineapple over the bottom of the pan.
Add layer of berries and sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over fruit.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit layers.
Top with generous amount of nuts.
Drizzle with melted butter. Finally, for a crunchy glaze, sprinkle the 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After pizza has cooked 25 minutes, take a spoon and cut down throughout the pizza in many places to permit juice to come up.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: In a large pot of water, covering about half of the cabbage, bring to a boil, then turn cabbage head.
Boil about 5 minutes until soft and pliable.
Mix ground beef, rice, onion and a few of the tomatoes that have been crushed.
Into bottom of a large pot, pour the sauerkraut.
Take off 1 leaf of cabbage at a time. Place a small ball of meat mixture in center. Wrap leaf like a little package.

Lay on top of sauerkraut with folded side down. Continue until all meat is used. Pour remaining tomatoes (crushed) over cabbage rolls. Cook on slow burner for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Keeps well. Recipe may be doubled.
Goes good with mashed potatoes and corn bread.

title: potato balls
directions: Rub potatoes through a sieve.
Add eggs, salt and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make the mixture stiff enough to shape into small balls.
Fry in hot fat; drain and serve hot.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Add 1 cup of peanut butter. Mix.
Take off burner, then add 1 package traditional Chex mix. Put in a large bowl with powdered sugar and shake up.
Spread on wax paper and let cool.
Serve in a dog food bowl.

title: onion bread
directions: Put water in a large bowl.
Add yeast; stir.
Add onion, sugar, salt, shortening, oregano and two cups of flour.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour.
Let rise 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for about an hour.
Cool.

title: triple orange fluff(low-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in sherbet. Refrigerate until partially set. Fold in whipped topping. Place cake in dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Arrange oranges over cake and pour gelatin mix over the top. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Makes 15 servings.

title: apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients and mix them well. Mix well the eggs, sugar (or substitute) and oil.
Add the dry ingredients and mix.
Add the apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° in an 11 1/2 x 17-inch greased pan for 25 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Stir.
Add juice and cold water.
Add almond extract.
Chill thoroughly.
To serve, pour into punch bowl.
Stir in sherbet and finish with ginger ale poured slowly.
Will make 5 quarts or 40 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: never fail buttercream icing
directions: Add ingredients in order, beating constantly until light and fluffy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and chopped onion to desired doneness; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, crumbling the crackers very fine.
Add a little grated cheese to the mixture, reserving some for the top.
Mix and pour into casserole dish; top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: manwich pizza
directions: Combine ground beef and Manwich according to instructions on can.
Prepare crust according to directions.
Spread Manwich over crust.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer in 2-quart container. Pour marinade on and chill.

title: rice nut loaf
directions: Mix together the ingredients like a meat loaf and bake at 300° for one hour.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, oil and water.
Bring to a boil. Cool a few minutes.
Drain the beans, peas and corn.
Add celery, onions and bell pepper.
Toss together to mix.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight and stir occasionally.
This keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: asparagus-english pea casserole
directions: Layer
asparagus, peas and soup in casserole.
Dot each layer with
butter.
Top	with
crushed
crackers and butter. Beat egg and
mix with milk.
Pour over vegetables and crackers.
Put thin layer of grated cheese on top and bake in 450° oven until
bubbly hot.
Put
on
another layer of cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into greased pan.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Method:
Mix meat with catsup, spices, eggs and water.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until golden.
Add to meat and mix thoroughly.
Form into balls 1-inch in diameter and brown in rest of butter.
Cover and cook over low flame about 20 minutes, turning when needed (once or twice). Makes about 60 meatballs.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and press in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add egg yolks to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes three 9-inch pans.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix it with tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix in a casserole dish.
Cover with both cheeses and pepperoni.
Completely cover entire mixture with crescent rolls.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until rolls are golden brown.

title: sunday slaw
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: In large pot, place a layer of tomatoes and sprinkle with salt. Then add a layer of onions and red peppers; salt.
Continue layers until vegetables are done.
Let stand overnight; drain well.
Cover with vinegar and spices.
Boil slowly 4 or 5 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; leave slightly undercooked.
Drain.
Blend together egg whites, skim milk, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, white pepper and parsley.
Mix sauce with macaroni and spoon into 1-quart baking dish sprayed with vegetable spray.

title: traveling jello salad
directions: Blend cherry pie mix, pineapple, jello and gelatin and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add nuts and celery.
Mold and chill.
Can be served 1 to 8 days after making.
Does not melt easily.

title: banana-pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (do not use mixer).
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake about
1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: hermits
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add raisins and set aside.
Sift together the flour, spices, salt and soda.
Add alternately with mixture of milk and molasses.
Divide dough into fourths and shape each section into roll 12 inches long.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake 15 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and potatoes skillet dinner
directions: In large, deep skillet, add olive oil and butter, then saute onion for 3 to 4 minutes over medium-high heat, then add garlic. Stir and heat another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add potatoes and sausage, salt, pepper and water.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and cook for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally and scraping the bottom to prevent sticking and scorching.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: lumberjack beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Add ground beef to bacon and cook until pink is gone but not brown.
Add beans, tomatoes, spaghetti, the first brown sugar, parsley, oregano, celery, salt and pepper. Put in baking dish.
Put onions on top.
Add last brown sugar and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 24 muffin pan cups with fluted liners. In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, mix flour, sugars, baking powder and salt until combined. Add milk, peanut butter, margarine or butter, vanilla and eggs; beat until blended. Beat 1 to 2 minutes or until creamy. Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Immediately remove cupcakes from pan to cool. When cool, frost and enjoy!

title: brickle
directions: Crush saltines and spread into bottom of glass baking dish. Boil sugar and butter; pour it over crushed saltines.
Sprinkle with chips and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon over medium-high heat for 2 minutes (bacon will not be done); remove bacon from skillet, reserving drippings in skillet.
Flatten chicken slightly with palm of hand, season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Place 4 chicken breasts in bacon drippings.
Cook 6 minutes on each side or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate this chicken for another day.
Return bacon to skillet.
Add remaining 4 chicken breasts and cook bacon until crisp and chicken is no longer pink in center.
Add tomatoes, olives and garlic salt.
Cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: date balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: miracle pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add baking powder, vanilla and sugar.
Add Ritz crackers and pecans.
Pour into highly greased pie pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: swedish meatballs in sauce
directions: Mix well with hands and form into 30 meatballs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 25 minutes. (Cut one open to see if it is cooked inside.) These may be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together. Chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add other ingredients; beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas beef stew
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, brown beef, adding oil if desired and drain.
Add onion, garlic powder, pepper and water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is almost tender.
Add tomatoes, cumin, and salt and return to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes until meat is tender (cook until tomatoes and onions are thick).
Yield: 4 servings (1 quart).

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Coat a wok or large nonstick skillet with Cooking Spray; drizzle Oil around top of wok.
Heat at medium-high heat (375) until hot.
Add Chicken, and stir-fry 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from wok, and drain well on paper towels.
Add Onion and next 8 ingredients; stir-fry 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Return Chicken to wok; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 (2-1/4-cups) servings.

title: chili-cheese balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 dozen at 30 calories each.

title: robert and kim's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and hollow out the mushrooms (as many as you want).
Mix cream cheese, green onions and bacon.
Kim tells Robert, "Take them little devils and stuff them!"
Bake at 375° until heated through.

title: harvest table apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry for two-crust 9-inch pie.
Fill bottom shell with 6 medium apples, sliced.
Combine cornstarch, cinnamon, salt, sugar, melted margarine and 1/3 cup Karo syrup.
Pour over apples. Cover with top crust and bake in 425° oven for 45 minutes or until crust is browned and apples are tender.
Remove from oven. To top, mix brown sugar, flour, 2 tablespoons Karo syrup, soft margarine and nuts.
Spread over top crust; return to oven for 10 minutes or until top is bubbly.

title: texas sheet bar
directions: Cake:
Fits 17 x 11 x 1-inch pan.
Boil together 2 sticks margarine, water and 4 heaping tablespoonfuls cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Add, beating after each addition, flour, sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creole black beans
directions: Combine ingredients except sausage and put in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 8 hours or high for 4 hours. Remove bay leaves. Serve over cooked rice.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.
Serve with sliced apple, banana or other fruit.

title: angel pie
directions: Dissolve the package of gelatin in cold water.
Set aside.
Mix flour and sugar in a saucepan.
Add milk gradually to avoid lumps. Add salt and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add gelatin and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let cool.
Beat 3 egg whites stiff with 3 teaspoons ice water.
Add 1/3 cup sugar.
Add cooled custard to egg whites; fold gently.
Place into vanilla wafer pie shell; cool until firm.
Top with Cool Whip and chocolate shavings.

title: italian tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust 10 minutes at 350°. Remove and sprinkle 1/2 cup Mozzarella in bottom; let melt as it cools. Cut tomatoes in wedges and drain on paper towel. Chop garlic. Mix remaining Mozzarella, Parmesan and mayo. Place wedges in crust, sprinkle garlic, then basil on top of tomatoes. Smooth mayo mixture over all. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: coconut rice
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan. Add coconut and cook and stir until browned. Add onion and cook 1 minute. Stir in rice. Add broth and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Remove from heat. Stir in mango. Sprinkle with chives.

title: strawberry-rhubarb puff
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, mix rhubarb, strawberries and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Place in oven.

title: sunday meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/2 can tomato sauce, mustard, brown sugar and vinegar in bowl; blend well.
Set aside.
Mix beef, sausage, eggs, onion, salt, pepper and stuffing mix with 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Shape into loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting with the prepared sauce every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In large skillet saute onion and beef until brown.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Simmer covered, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.

title: luby's cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese and onions throughly.
Put about 1/4 c. of mixture on each tortilla and roll semi-tight, about the size of a quarter.
Place in 2-9x13-inch pans.
Keep covered in refrigerator until ready to use.
Pour the chili over the enchiladas in each pan.
Cover with foil and cook in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Remove foil and sprinkle the top with American cheese.
Cook until just melted.
Serves 8 (2 enchiladas per serving).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and oleo together. Add eggs and beat well.
Add pumpkin and water.
Continue beating. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quickie cream puffs
directions: Boil water and margarine.
Add flour; mix vigorously.
Remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Drop from a tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or fork.
Add the eggs and enough milk to make a dough that holds together and can be kneaded.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside. Cream shortening; gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar, beating well. Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar in medium mixing bowl.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in reserved sugar cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased pans.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Add eggs and juice; mix well.
Pour into crust; bake 50 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream; bake 5 minutes longer. Chill.
Serve with Raspberry Topping.

title: "date chewies"
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Add to butter mixture, mixing until blended.
Stir in nuts and dates.

title: green beans with tomatoes
directions: Heat the olive oil in a saucepan.
Add the onion and garlic and cook gently, stirring for 4 to 5 minutes, taking care that they don't brown.
Stir in the sugar and cook for another minute, then add the tomatoes, bay leaf, allspice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: broccoli corn delight
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch, 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix tomato sauce with macaroni.
Brown sausage, onion and green pepper together.
Mix in pizza sauce with all ingredients. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: red kidney bean salad
directions: Thoroughly rinse and drain kidney beans.
Combine vinegar, oil, oregano, salt and pepper; mix with beans.
Blend in celery and onion; chill.
Serve in crisp lettuce cups.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Put water on to boil and cook spaghetti as directed on box. In the meantime, cut bacon in small pieces and fry until done. After spaghetti is cooked, rinse and drain in colander.
In a large casserole dish, put a layer of spaghetti in bottom of dish followed by salt and pepper, pieces of bacon, crushed tomatoes and sharp cheese.
Repeat again, ending with sharp cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
Let cool and punch holes in it with a fork.
While cake is baking, mix jello with 3/4 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Let cool to room temperature.
When cake is cooled, pour jello mixture through the holes.

title: pumpkin cheese bake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, on low speed, combine cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and 2 teaspoons pie spice until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk, then remaining 2 eggs, pumpkin, 2 teaspoons spice and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over crust; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Chill; cut into bars.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line bottom with 1 layer pie crust in greased 7 x 11-inch dish. Make sure sides are covered.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes at 450°.
Cook vegetables and drain.
Cook onion and mushrooms in pan in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add water, milk and chicken bouillon all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in vegetables, chicken and parsley; heat until bubbly.
Fill crust-lined baking dish; place second pie crust on top.
Pinch edges together.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nana simpson's congo bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt (dry ingredients).
Melt oleo; add brown sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Let cool slightly (about 10 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Now add dry ingredients, then nuts and chips.
Place in greased 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Measure and sift flour, salt and soda.
Then add to first mixture.
Stir in remaining vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for one hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice of pineapple and add water to make 1 1/2 cups. Drain juice of oranges to make 1/2 cup.
Add juices to vanilla pudding mix and cook to make glaze.
Add to oranges and pineapple. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add remaining fruit.
Top with slices of kiwi fruit (optional).

title: philly pineapple pie
directions: Place cheese in bowl and cream until soft and smooth.
Blend in sugar and salt; add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly. Blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread preserves over bottom of shell. Spread cheese mixture next.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then reduce heat to 325° and bake 50 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole. Let stand in refrigerator overnight or 6 to 8 hours or freeze. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: company's coming meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup.
Form into a loaf.
Cover bottom of baking dish with ketchup (about 1/2 inch deep).
Place in preheated 350° oven and bake approximately 1 hour.
The ketchup and juices from the meat blend and make a wonderful tomato sauce to serve over meat loaf.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a large pan layer wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.

title: spicy calico beans
directions: Saute
the
bacon,
beef
and onion until browned.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach and brown rice salad
directions: Cook brown rice.
Pour one cup Newman's Own into brown rice and refrigerate, covered.
Prepare spinach, chopped scallions, chopped celery, drained garbanzo beans, crumbled Feta cheese and cubed tomato into large salad bowl.
Cook turkey bacon in microwave 5 to 6 minutes or until done.
Crumble on top of salad. When ready to serve, pour brown rice mixture over salad and toss. Croutons to season.
Enjoy!

title: date filled cookies
directions: Combine dates and water in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans.
Cool.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Dissolve soda in pulp and beaten egg.
Add to first mixture.
Sift flour with spices; combine with persimmon mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: curried turkey and broccoli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Arrange in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with turkey.
Mix soup, mayo, juice and curry powder.
Pour over turkey.
Mix baking mix and egg just until crumbly; sprinkle on top.
Drizzle with margarine.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until mixture is hot and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg; mix in flour, soda, spices and sour milk.
Bake at 350° in small pan until toothpick comes out clean.
Use a buttercream icing.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in water.
Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening thoroughly.
Add buttermilk in dissolved yeast and mix with spoon until flour is moistened.
Take out enough for a meal, roll on floured board, cut with cutter and place in shallow greased pan.
Let raise and bake about 12 to 16 minutes. Place remaining dough in refrigerator.

title: zucchini with mushrooms
directions: Cut zucchini in 1/2-inch slices and then cut them in half. Slice mushrooms thin (if fresh ones).
Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add all but parsley.
Saute, uncovered, until tender. Sprinkle with parsley at serving time.
Serves 6.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Combine the other ingredients.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Add dry ingredients and mincemeat.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yield:
5 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Top with crushed corn flakes (2 cups).
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and pour over the top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Beat egg lightly; add milk and set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, mustard and salt.
Mix together and then add vinegar.
In a saucepan, combine the two mixtures.
Over medium heat, stir until dressing thickens.
Cool.
Refrigerate.
I combine this dressing with Miracle Whip when making potato salad. Delicious and zesty.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and whipping cream; pour in freezer can.
Add Eagle Brand milk and stir.
Add milk to fill line.
To add fruit, reduce milk.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs, nuts and apples.
Add no liquid, just stir (will get thinner as you stir).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Using a flameproof, ovenproof covered casserole, brown the salted chops in oil.
Cover with rice.
Combine soup and milk and pour over rice, making sure all rice is moistened.
Cover tightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: jeweled shortbread cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugar and almond extract until fluffy.
Stir in combined oats and flour.
Divide dough into four equal pieces.
Place two portions on opposite corners of a large ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each into circle about 1/8-inch thick.
Press edges of dough with tines of fork.
Repeat with other two pieces.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from oven; spread 2 tablespoons preserves on center of each circle.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon almonds over preserves.
Cool 10 minutes on cookie sheet.
With large knife, cut each circle into 8 wedges.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Store loosely covered.
Yields 32 servings.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour one 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, brown sugar and oats.
Add apple, nuts, raisins, eggs, milk and oil.
Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, or until done.
Cool on wire rack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; place in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Ingredients may be layered.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: saucy beef over rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in 1 (14 x 20-inch) oven bag.
Place in baking pan.
Add undrained tomatoes, soup mix, water and pepper to bag.
Turn bag to coat beef with sauce.
Arrange ingredients in even layer.
Close bag.
Cut 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake until beef is tender, 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tropical cake
directions: Start oven at 300°.
Grease loaf pan and line with wax paper. In a large mixing bowl, combine nuts, dates and cherries.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over fruit-nut mixture and mix about with your hands until all ingredients are well coated. Beat eggs until frothy, then add vanilla.
Pour mixture over fruit and nuts.
Put in loaf pan and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: drop molasses cookies
directions: Sift 6 cups flour with salt and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat until light.
Add molasses and vinegar, then dry ingredients.
Lastly, add soda dissolved in hot water. Cool and then drop by small tablespoon.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and cover with water.
Cook 2 to 3 hours until thick.

title: chess cake
directions: Butter pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients and pat out in bottom of pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over first layer.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle while hot with powdered sugar.

title: potato puff
directions: Blend all ingredients until potatoes are finely grated and turn into buttered casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about an hour. If this seems too big a load for your blender, blend 2 cut potatoes and 1/2 cup milk first; turn into casserole.
Blend other ingredients and mix.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions, garlic and celery until tender in butter.
Add flour and cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add water, tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally 25 minutes or until sauce is almost of desired consistency.
Add shrimp and continue cooking 15 minutes.
Serve with parsley rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs with butter.
Press into an 8 inch pie pan.
(Save a few crumbs to sprinkle over the top when done.)

title: my grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugar gradually. Add egg and beat well. Add remaining ingredients that have been sifted together.
Mix thoroughly.
Mold into balls using rounded teaspoonful of dough.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten with fork (crisscross).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: butter cookies(lemon glaze)
directions: Note:
Amounts in parentheses are for recipe cut in half.

title: pound cake with apple-honey cream
directions: Mix applesauce with cinnamon and cardamom; chill.
Whip sour cream until fluffy; fold in honey and orange rind.
Chill.
Toast both sides of pound cake slices.
Top with banana slices.
Heap applesauce mixture over bananas and top with a spoon of sour cream.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pecan halves.

title: june's sweet potato topping
directions: Combine and sprinkle over drained sweet potatoes.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage fine.
Add salt and mix in large bowl.
Set aside for 1 hour.

While waiting, prepare remaining vegetables. Make a syrup of sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed and boil for 1 minute until sugar is dissolved and cool to lukewarm. Drain cabbage and squeeze to remove water.
Pour syrup over all vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Pack in desired containers.
Zip each freezer bag, etc.

title: chicken breasts in tarragon cream
