directions: Rinse chicken and dry well.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a large heavy skillet over medium heat; add chicken and brown on both sides, about 10 minutes total.
Stir onions into butter.
Add 1 tablespoon of the wine.
Cover and cook over low heat just until chicken loses translucency and is tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove chicken to warm platter; keep warm.
Add remaining wine, tarragon and cream to pan.
Cook and stir over high heat until liquid reduces to consistency of heavy cream.
Taste and correct seasoning; stir in some parsley, if desired, and pour over chicken.

title: nancy powell's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, then milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to mixture and drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven until light brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Mix the dry ingredients. Cut in shortening as for biscuit dough.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture; blend thoroughly.
Turn the dough out onto a floured cloth and knead as for regular biscuits.
Roll out and cut biscuits. Place biscuits in a greased pan.
Let dough rise for a few minutes before baking.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400° or until brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain and add salt, pepper, oregano, red pepper and powdered garlic.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer. Cook noodles about 20 minutes.
Drain noodles and add butter so they don't stick.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add.
Add lemon juice to mashed bananas.
(This keeps the bananas light and fluffy.)
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven, 375°, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix and make into roll;
refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard the small
tips
of each wing.
Cut the main wing bone and second
wing bone at the joint.	Sprinkle the wings with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in deep-fryer or deep saucepan to about 350°.
Add
some of the wings.
(Do not overcrowd.) Deep fry, turning,
until
golden brown and crisp, about 10 minutes.
Drain well
on
paper
towel.
Repeat
with remaining
wings.	Melt
butter
in
a
small
saucepan.
Add desired
amount of hot sauce
and
vinegar.
Put
hot
chicken wings onto warm serving platter.
Put mixture over all.
Serve immediately with desired dressing
and celery sticks.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Use Blue Cheese Dressing, see index.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Bring oleo, cocoa and water mixture to rolling boil and then pour over flour mixture. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and bake on 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: special hamburger
directions: Mix beef, green pepper, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Moisten bread slices with water and add to mixture along with cracker crumbs; should be moist.
Form patties, fry in medium heat until done.
Cover with ketchup.
Let simmer, then turn.
Pour ketchup on other side; simmer.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in pan.
Heat to boiling point. Remove and add jello.
Mix well.
Set aside and cool to room temperature.
Stir in cottage cheese and fold in topping. Let set several hours before serving.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce and ground beef in bowl.
Cover bottom of lasagne dish with 2 cups sauce.
Arrange layer of uncooked noodles.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour remaining sauce evenly to cover.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and let set several hours or overnight to soak noodles.
(If overnight, refrigerate.) Remove plastic wrap and cover with foil for part of the baking time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer or until knife goes easily through the pasta.
Let stand covered for at least 10 minutes to thicken and set before serving.
Serves 12 generously. If your baking pan is deep enough it could be done in three layers.
Water may be added to sauce if it needs to go further.

title: low-fat refried beans
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, cook the onion in the oil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until soft and beginning to color, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook, stirring often, until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add 1/3 of the beans and 1/4 cup of the chicken broth. Coarsely mash the beans with a potato masher or a wooden spoon.
Add another 1/3 of the beans and 1/4 cup broth; mash. Add the remaining beans and another 1/4 cup broth and mash those beans, too.
Stir in the remaining 1/4 cup broth and season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a simmer over medium heat and cook, stirring almost constantly with a wooden spoon until the beans are very thick, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crisp oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes to coat thoroughly. Bake, stirring potatoes occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: recipe for christian home
directions: Take one God, one Savior and one Bible with a generous portion of the Spirit of God.
Mix with 1 Loving Mother and one God-fearing Father.
Add any number of respectful children.
Place all under roof.
Stir in a pinch of discipline as needed.
Combine in spiritual atmosphere of the Church.
Fold in generous amounts of affection and worship and service.
Bake until eternally bonded. Try it.
It is a sure thing.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a baking dish. Grease the dish and flour it a little.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour bundt pan.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well for 5 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: deep-dish taco squares
directions: Grease	an
x
x 2-inch square baking dish.
Cook ground beef until brown;	drain.	Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and
onion;
reserve.
Mix	baking mix and water until soft
dough forms.
Pat
into pan, pressing dough 1/2-inch up sides.
Layer beef,
tomatoes and green pepper in pan.
Spoon sour
cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: blackberry roll with egg sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Toss gently with blackberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter and fold the extra crust over the berries.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes. Cool and serve with egg sauce.

title: dip for veggies
directions: Beat all together with electric mixer until smooth.

title: cleda's jalapeno rice
directions: Cook rice with 2 tablespoons butter in 2 cups water.
When done, add rest of ingredients.
Bake in a buttered dish for 30 minutes at 300°.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture; mix.
Add eggs, water, vanilla and mix. Stir in mincemeat and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Shape into loaf and place in ovenproof casserole dish or pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Great with mashed potatoes, rolls and salad for a healthy meal.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Cook potatoes (but not mushy).
Pour sauce over and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Can be cooked in microwave.

title: antiqued flowers
directions: For darker, add 2 tablespoons dark oak varnish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from pan.
Break chicken up, removing skin and place in casserole dish.
Pour both cans of cream of chicken soup over top with about 1/3 cup water; mix well.
Make stuffing as package directs.
Pour over chicken and soup.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6 persons.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Place in bottom of covered dish. Place thin slices of potatoes over chops after peeling. Cover with Cheddar
cheese soup (undiluted) and top with onion soup. Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit pies
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix milk, lemon juice, Cool Whip and fruit (in this order).
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: earl's easy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets.
While still warm, cut potatoes into bite sized pieces.
Add seasonings and dressings. Mix until well blended.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
You can also cook this in the microwave.

title: m. b.'s baked spaghetti dish
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix cottage cheese and cream cheese with hot spaghetti; add onion, pepper and mushrooms to mixture.
Add ketchup and mix together. Put in a casserole dish.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: make-ahead layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in order.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread over entire top.
Sprinkle bacon bits over all.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate.
Chill 6 hours or more.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: "t"errific salisbury skillet
directions: Mix thoroughly the beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape firmly into 4 oval patties.
In skillet, brown patties (use shortening if necessary).
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally. Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make gelatin as usual; add cranberries.
When mixture begins to set, add sour cream.

title: ham barbecue sandwich(50 to 60 sandwiches)
directions: Cook chopped onion with oleo 5 to 10 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients (except ham).
Cook another 5 minutes.
Add ham and just heat.
Serve in hot round rolls.

title: pecan-chocolate chip pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar, butter (softened), eggs and almond extract on low just until mixed.
Beat on high for 5 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt on low speed.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, mixing just until blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Sprinkle pecans in the bottom of a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Carefully pour batter over pecans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes in pan before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix together and spread in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter and then in cracker crumbs.
Place in baking dish and bake at 375° for one hour, uncovered.
Do not turn chicken.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook in 2 1/2 quarts of water until tender.
Debone and cut meat into pieces.
Save broth and add 2 chicken bouillon cubes to broth.

title: joan's cream puffs
directions: In saucepan, heat water and margarine to boiling point.
Stir in flour.
Stir constantly over low heat until mixture leaves the pan and forms into a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat. Cool.
Beat in 1 at a time, the 4 eggs.
Beat mixture until smooth and velvety.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until dry.
Allow to cool slowly. Makes 8 large puffs.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Spread rice evenly in bottom of a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 onion soup mix or 1/2 of chopped onion.
Place chicken on rice; sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix or chopped onion and pepper.
Combine soups and water; blend well and pour over chicken.
Cover; bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Very good!

title: brunch cake
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream well.
Add to cake mix.
Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
(I used Duncan Hines Butter Recipe).
Mix frosting mix with melted butter (margarine); add to cake mix and stir into batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a tube or Bundt pan.
Test for doneness.
(May take longer due to differences in ovens).
Cool in pan for 25 minutes; turn onto plate and cool completely.

title: homas house kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add pinch of salt. Beat until egg whites peak. Add brown sugar gradually, beating after each time. Fold in chopped pecans. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
While the hamburger is cooking, open the can of biscuits and butter one side.
Cut the biscuits into halves and put aside.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce to the hamburger and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 3/4 package of Mozzarella cheese and can of mixed vegetables.
Mix well so that cheese is well melted.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Stir in potato chips. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° from 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden.
When cooled, sift powdered sugar on all sides.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture is thick and clear; cool.
Beat three egg whites with 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract until soft mounds form.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Continue beating until meringue stands in stiff peaks.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix all together and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
I use Velveeta cheese and stewed Mexican tomatoes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break up cake.
Mix sugar, milk, Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Stir into cake.
Mix strawberries into glaze (drain strawberries).
Layer cake and strawberries mixture into punch bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Hand roll into pecan size balls. Bake at 350° until brown.
Very, very good.
Use toothpick to pick up with.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill cupcake cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit summer soup
directions: Mix and whisk first four ingredients.
Chill.
Put fruit into bowls and add soup.

title: peanut delight dessert(sinfully delicious)
directions: Blend flour and margarine together. Add chopped nuts and press evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Set aside and cool.

title: salmon quiche
directions: For crust, combine the whole-wheat flour, the 2/3 cup cheese, the almonds, salt and paprika in a bowl. Stir in oil. Set aside 1/2 cup of the crust mixture. Press remaining mixture into the bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake crust in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Mix ingredients, using 1 cup nuts.
Chill. Form a ball and roll in remaining 1 cup nuts.

title: shrimp-crabmeat casserole
directions: Boil shrimp.
Mix shrimp, crabmeat, onion, celery and mayo together.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Place in buttered casserole. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cover with potato chip crumbs and paprika.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve chilled over baked potatoes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and sift together; flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add bananas; mix well.
Add 1/4 of the flour mixture at a time; beat until smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into a well greased loaf pan.
Bake 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool on rack before slicing.

title: mint chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine cookie crumbs and margarine. Press firmly in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: vanilla sugar
directions: Grind vanilla bean in blender until finely flaked. Add sugar and process until mixture reaches fine consistency. Store in tightly sealed jar. This is wonderful on fresh fruit or French toast.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix orange jello with cottage cheese.
Add fruit, then Cool Whip.

title: egg salad sandwiches supreme
directions: Combine ingredients and moisten well with mayonnaise.
Spread on buttered bread and add lettuce. Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken without adding salt.
Place cooked and deboned chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup and chicken broth.
Warm and pour over chicken.
Combine flour, baking powder, milk and butter. Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Simmer all ingredients until done.
Remove chicken from pot and take meat from the bones.
Discard skin and bones and put meat back in the broth.
Add 10 medium potatoes, peeled and diced. Cook until done.
Line sheet cake pan with plain biscuit dough. With slotted spoon, dip potatoes and meat into pan and cover with top crust.
Make 6 slits in top crust and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until top crust is brown.
If you have any dough leftover, roll out 1/4-inch thick and slice 1/2-inch wide.
Put noodles in broth and cook 15 minutes.
Spoon this on your plate over pot pie.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: nutty baklava
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cut phyllo in half crosswise.
Cut into half to fit into pan.
Discard trimmings. Cover phyllo with slightly damp towel.
Layer 10 sheets of phyllo in pan, brushing each sheet with melted butter.

title: glazed roasted pecans
directions: Put oil and white Karo in iron skillet and as soon as it boils, turn
fire
off and add pecan halves and stir until well coated.
Put on
cookie
sheet
and
cook for 1 hour in 200° or 225° oven.
Stir
every
15 minutes.
Pour out on foil and salt to taste.

title: chicken-corn soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, debone and return to stock.
Add noodles, corn and parsley; simmer for 15 minutes.
Drop in chopped eggs and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into an unbaked pie shell. Bake in 375° oven until golden brown or about 50 minutes.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Combine
hamburger,
salt,
milk,
crumbs,	catsup, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Shape into loaf in center of 9 x 13-inch
pan
that is foil lined.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick the
potatoes
and	onions.
Peel and quarter lengthwise the carrots.
Mix
parsley
flakes,
1 teaspoon salt and a few grains of	pepper.
Place vegetables in layers around meat and sprinkle each layer with part of salt mixture.

title: fettuccine and garden vegetable sauce
directions: Gradually add fettuccine and salt to rapidly boiling water so that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until tender.
Drain.
While fettuccine is cooking, in large bowl, combine tomatoes, zucchini and chives.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss immediately with hot fettuccine. Add freshly ground black pepper.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: double stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; pat dry. Pierce each potato several times with a fork. Microwave on high for about 10 minutes or until tender. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt butter in a medium skillet over low heat. Add onion to skillet; cook about 5 minutes. Slice off precooked potato tops. Scoop out potatoes, keeping shells intact and place pulp into medium bowl. Mash potato pulp; add onions, 1/2 cup cheddar, sour cream, chives, pepper and salt to taste. Spoon potato mixture into shells, dividing evenly. Sprinkle potatoes with remaining 1/4 cup cheddar. Place in medium casserole. Bake potatoes until heated through, about 10 minutes.

title: chicken dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Layer as listed. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour in 9 x 13 glass pan.

title: peel in simple syrup
directions: Over low heat, simmer water, sugar and mandarin peel.
Cook until sugar is dissolved, mixture is slightly thickened and mandarin peel is limp and vivid orange.
Cool, store in a covered container in the refrigerator.
This syrup will keep for up to 6 months and is a great topping for ice cream or pound cake and makes a dramatic garnish for pork, poultry and fish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix vanilla yogurt and cream cheese.
Add cherry Jell-O powder for color.
Serve with your favorite fruit.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Blend butter with the white and brown sugars, the eggs and vanilla. Blend in rest of ingredients. Make into balls and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes. Yield: 112 cookies.

title: pepper steak
directions: Stir-fry vegetables in oil until tender-crisp.
Remove from wok or skillet.
Cook steak in oil with seasonings.
When steak is done, add vegetables and stir-fry until hot.
Serve over hot rice.

title: olan's so-simple peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat egg well; add peanut butter, sugar and vanilla; mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mmmm-good!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the lard and sugar. Add the eggs
and mix well. Add the bananas and blend well. Add the flour and soda, sifted together. Add the nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 335° to 350°.
Let it set a few minutes in the pan and then turn out to cool. (The bread is better mixed by hand than with a mixer, though either method is all right.)
It is very good hot, cold or toasted.
May be rolled in foil and stored in refrigerator for a week or longer or it may be frozen for usage later.

title: cheesy potato slices
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place butter in a 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan.
Place in oven until butter melts.
Add potatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Toss until potatoes are thoroughly coated. Spread out into an even layer.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn; sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese.
Continue baking for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, crusty and golden brown.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread bean mixture evenly in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with large corn chips.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Set aside.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Roll sandwiches in egg mixture and then in potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken, skin and debone.
Cut to bite-size pieces.
Reserve stock after removing fat.
Saute green peppers, onion and celery in margarine.
Cook noodles in chicken stock.
Mix together cheese (reserve a little cheese for topping), pimento, mushrooms, mushroom soup, 1 cup chicken stock, salt and pepper to taste.
Add to noodles.
Put in large pan and top with reserved cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix dressing, juice and seasoning mix.
Place chicken breasts on broiler rack.
Brush with 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Broil for 8-10 minutes.
Turn chicken over and brush with remaining dressing mixture.
Continue broiling for 8-10 minutes until chicken juices run clear.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Hat water and cinnamon drops until melted.
Put in raspberry Jell-O; mix and cool.
Add applesauce (sweetened) and pineapple. (In summer, use 1/2 package Knox gelatine.)
The applesauce and pineapple take care of liquid you would use in the Jell-O.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate fluff
directions: Layer 1:
Blend butter, flour and walnuts.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Uncover and cook until desired consistency.
Serve with buttered noodles. Serves 6.

title: jello delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar, salt, lemon juice and rind.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Meanwhile, whip milk until stiff.
Beat jello mixture into whipped milk.
Put 1/2 of graham cracker crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour jello mixture evenly over crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Chill several hours before serving.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg.
In a mixing bowl, combine the milk, egg and melted margarine.
Add the orange juice, rind, chopped apples (skins may be left on) and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into milk mixture with a spoon until blended.
Do not overmix!

title: african rum buns
directions: Mix butter, flour and all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, rum and vanilla extract.
Mix and add milk.
Drop 1 tablespoon batter onto 2 greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach surprise
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients and then turn off. Add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add peaches.
Put in refrigerator to
set.
Can top with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Slice bread not quite in two, making a pocket.
Spread soft cream cheese on one side and jam on the other.
Prepare as usual, dipping in egg and cooking on a griddle.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from thawed turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on a cutting board, placing the skin side down.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: deli hot liverwurst sandwich
directions: Layer ingredients on bread and grill in hot frying pan with butter like you would do a grilled cheese sandwich.
Makes 1 delicious sandwich.

title: meatballs from bari, italy
directions: Slightly moisten bread crumbs with water. Combine all ingredients mixing well.
Form meat mixture into 2 inch balls.

title: sugar, sugar cookies
directions: Mix and sift sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter until soft.
Beat in sugar, egg, vanilla and milk.
Add to flour mixture, mixing well.
Wrap the dough in foil or plastic wrap and chill thoroughly (30 minutes).
Place on lightly floured board and roll out to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut with cutter, dipped in flour, then place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake in 375° oven about 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients; cut in the margarine with a pastry blender until the flour is crumbly.
Beat the egg and the buttermilk with the raisins; add to the dry ingredients and blend until just mixed.
Knead until smooth.
Divide into 2 loaves. Place in an 8-inch pan.
Press down lightly.
Cut cross in top. Bake at 350° for about 35 or 40 minutes.

title: mint chocolate coffee
directions: Combine 1 cup nondairy coffee creamer-powder, confectioners sugar and cocoa.
Add chocolate extract and mint extract.
Beat at low speed until thoroughly blended.
Stir in mint chocolate mixture into a cup of hot coffee.
The mint chocolate mixture can be stored into an airtight container.

title: sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water to al dente.
Mix soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and Worcestershire sauce and heat through.
Cool thoroughly.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chicken dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made the day before or can be frozen.
Serves 12.

title: basic dip for appetizers
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings to blend smooth.

title: wild mushroom saute
directions: Heat oil in a medium size saucepan.
Add shallot; cook over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms, thyme and oregano; saute 30 seconds.
Add chicken broth.
Season with salt and pepper. Simmer 15 minutes or until mushrooms are softened.
Makes 1 serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand several hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake a yellow cake in sheet cake pan.
Use a large glass salad bowl or smaller punch bowl.
Crumble cake and put 1/3 in bottom of bowl.
Make 3 layers:

title: jack-o-lantern punch
directions: Dissolve both envelopes of Kool-Aid and the sugar in 3 quarts ice water in a nonmetal pitcher.
Add the chilled ginger ale. Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift flour and cinnamon together.
Blend eggs and sugar together; add pumpkin and oil.
Blend and then add flour and nuts. Preheat oven to 350° and bake 1 hour.

title: toffee squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, vanilla, flour and salt; mix well.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Melt chocolate in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spread over hot bars.
Sprinkle immediately with nuts.
Cool; cut into 1-1/4 inch squares.

title: dad's favorite pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon or pour onto a lightly greased skillet on high to medium heat.

title: cornish hens dijon
directions: In a rectangle baking dish, split 2 hens in half and place in baking dish, skin side up.
Brush hens evenly with mustard. Season with pepper.
Arrange potatoes, 4 on each side and prick each one 4 times.
Pour wine over.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.

title: potica cake
directions: Melt margarine and milk.
Let cool.
Mix yeast and warm water. Add yeast to milk.
Add 3 yolks to milk mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar, salt and flour.
Mix well.
(If dough seems real sticky, add a little more flour.)
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour in oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon.
Let set several minutes.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt together butter and marshmallows.
Add green food coloring.
Pour mixture over and coat the corn flakes.
Drop onto waxed paper with a teaspoon.
Add cinnamon candy or M&M's on top.

title: s'more cereal squares
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook corn syrup to boiling or place in large microwave-safe bowl and microwave at High for 1 minute or to boiling.
Remove from heat or microwave oven; add chocolate and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Gradually fold in cereal until coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows.
Press mixture into prepared pan; refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Refrigerate leftover bars to retain crispness.
Makes about 24 bars.

title: cocoa gravy
directions: Put water in a sauce pan and bring to a boil. Stir together dry ingredients until well mixed and lump free. Stir into boiling water and boil until thickened, stirring constantly. If too thick, add water to suit your taste.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients as directed.
Fold in Cool Whip, then cut bananas in pudding.
Layer pudding and vanilla wafers.
Top with Cool Whip or pudding mix.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In saucepan bring water and bouillon cube to a boil.
Add broccoli and carrot.
Cook according to broccoli directions and remove from heat.
Do not drain.
In separate pan melt butter and stir in flour.
Continue stirring while adding milk.
Stir in the cheese, soup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli mixture and cook over medium to low heat until desired thickness.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date nut chews
directions: Beat eggs, salt and almond extract.
Beat until light. Gradually beat in sugar and syrup.
Add dates and nuts.
Mix well. Fold in sifted flour.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch square cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until edges are brown. Remove from oven and, while hot, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: polish potato casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, melt the butter or margarine; stir in flour.
Cook, stirring, for 1 minute, then gradually add the milk, stirring constantly to eliminate lumps.
Cook the mixture over moderately low heat, stirring it, until the sauce begins to thicken.
Stir in the salt and pepper.
Set the sauce aside.

title: vegetable nachos with cilantro cream
directions: For Creamed Cilantro:
Stir together sour cream and cilantro or parsley.
Cover and set aside.

title: shortcake
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar to eggs.
Add pancake mix, vanilla and melted butter to eggs-sugar mixture.
Place wax paper in bottom of 10 x 15-inch pan.
Pour into pan and bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until puffed and set.
Turn out of pan, then cool.
You may add 3 teaspoons of cocoa, if desired, to pancake mix.

title: zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients and spices.
Stir in nuts. Pour into bread pans which have been greased only on the bottoms. Bake at 325° for 60 to 80 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Stir in chili, oregano, sugar, salt and garlic.
Blend in tomato paste.
Add tomato juice and onion; stir well.
Add water; bring to boil.
Add spaghetti; stir to separate strands.
Cover and simmer, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes.

title: donna's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts with chicken bouillon cubes, bay leaves and parsley until tender (20 to 30 minutes). Cut up chicken into small pieces.
Mix chicken with 1 can mushroom soup.
Mix in 1 (8-ounce) sour cream.
Place chicken mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix as directed Stove Top stuffing.
Place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: yum yum dessert
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with slices of angel food cake. Sprinkle can of pineapple with half the juice drained off over the cake.
Mix the pudding mix with 3 cups milk and pour over cake mixture.
Slice the banana thin and put on top
of pudding. Spread Cool Whip over all.

title: southern fruit salad
directions: Dice the apples and bananas.
Slice and add the grapes and lemon juice.
Stir in the oranges, marshmallows, pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into 8-inch square dish or mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Mix together soups and sour cream and heat.
Mix with chicken and noodles.
Put in casserole dish.
Brown 20 saltine crackers in 1/4 cups margarine in frypan.
Put this on top of casserole.
Cook at 400° until it starts to bubble.

title: old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Whip eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour and 1 teaspoon sugar over pie shell before filling.
Then pour filling into shell and bake in preheated oven at 300° until firm.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together.
Combine the melted butter and orange juice then add boiling water to make 3/4 cup. Mix liquid with dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg; mix well.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
One bag of cranberries makes 3 loaves.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except tea.
Mix instant tea in a cup of water or fruit juice and then add to mixture.
If this doesn't make 1 gallon, add enough water to make 1 gallon.
This gallon is your base.
To this add 2 gallons of water, making a total of 3 gallons of punch.
Freeze this mixture in containers in deep freeze.
When ready to use, take out long enough to thaw to a slush.
Before serving, add 1 small bottle of ginger ale to each punch bowl of punch.
Will serve approximately 80 punch cups.

title: country potato soup
directions: Peel and dice 3 cups potatoes.
Dice celery and onion. Combine these in large pot and add the water, bouillon cubes and salt.
Cover and cook 20 minutes. Add 1 cup milk.
In medium bowl, mix sour cream, flour, chives and the other cup of milk. Cook over low heat until thickens.
Makes 6 cups.

title: west of the pecos casserole
directions: Cook all but last four ingredients in heavy pan until meat is browned.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.
Put in casserole dish and let cool (this tends to thicken it).
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° until it bubbles.
This makes 2 casseroles, so you can freeze one, or if you have a large family, it will make one meal.

title: ants-on-a-log
directions: Wash celery and cut into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Spread peanut butter onto celery.
Place raisins on top of peanut butter!

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and egg; cream together. Add milk and vanilla. Cook over medium heat until thick. Add raisins which have been soaked in boiling water; drain. Add to custard. Put in baked pie shell. Cool.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Heat oven at
Grease
and flour 9 x 9 x 3/4-inch pan. Pour
hot
water
over dates; cool.
Combine shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat 5 minutes on high speed until fluffy.
Sift
together
flour, soda and salt.
On low speed or by
hand
add
in
flour in 4 additions with date mixture, ending
with
flour.
Blend
just
until smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Easy Penuche Frosting.

title: white cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Use enough flour to make dough roll and not stick to board or hands.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted margarine and graham crackers together and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, butter and vanilla for 10 minutes (important).
Add eggs and continue to beat until well blended.
Pour over graham crackers.
Slice bananas in halves and place on top of sugar mixture, then add crushed pineapple. Spread Cool Whip on top and garnish with chopped nuts.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Lightly oil 18 mini-muffin cups.
Stir together the flours, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Whisk together eggs, apple butter, vanilla and oil. Stir in apples, raisins and carrots.
Combine the two mixtures and stir just until moistened.
Spoon into the muffin cups (3/4 full). In a small bowl, combine walnuts and wheat germ; sprinkle over the muffin tops.
Bake for 15 -20 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Do not whip the cream.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Lay potatoes in casserole dish.
Put onion on top of potatoes. Pour mushroom soup over potatoes and onion.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: prairie rice hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until light brown; drain off fat. Add onions and green pepper; cook and stir until onions are tender. Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper; heat through. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake 45 minutes; add corn. Bake 15 more minutes.

title: baked marine dinner
directions: Combine the first 9
ingredients and place in a large, well-greased casserole.
Crumble the corn flakes over the top and over this pour the melted butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Uncover for the last 10 minutes of the cooking period to crisp the top.
Serve piping hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed spinach pizza
directions: Thaw bread dough and let rise according to package directions. Roll 2/3 down onto 11-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Line bottom and sides of greased 9-inch cake pan with dough.
Place tomatoes and sausage in pan.
Sprinkle with basil, oregano and pepper.
Combine Ricotta, spinach, Mozzarella, 3/4 cup Parmesan, garlic and salt; spread over tomatoes.
Roll remaining dough into 9-inch circle.
Place over cheese mixture.
Pinch edges to seal. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Spread with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add pizza sauce, stirring until hot.
Put on buns, add pepperoni and Mozzarella on top.
Pop into microwave until cheese melts.
Makes about 6 burgers.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soften the yeast in the lukewarm water. Add the salt and sugar. Add the flour and knead.
Do not let dough rise.
Cut into small pieces and roll in ropes (not too thick).
Twist into pretzel shapes, like praying arms.
Lay on foil covered cookie sheet dusted with flour. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 400° until golden, about 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 to 6 dozen.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and bell pepper and drain.
Pour into casserole dish with the corn.
Add 1/2 cup cornmeal and a glass of water.
Bake at 350° until cornmeal is brown.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Cook in saucepan the sugar and flour until thick.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Mix and spread on cake.

title: grandma sobek's casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Brown meat in pan and add sauce, salt and pepper; set aside.
Blend well the cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and parsley.
Butter pan and spread 1/2 noodles, then the creamed cheeses, then the rest of the noodles.
Sprinkle with melted butter.
Top with meat.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix potatoes, liquid, sugar, yeast, salt and 1/2 the flour. Beat well.
Add rest of the flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise once.
Shape and bake.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir butter, Parmesan cheese and egg into hot spaghetti.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cook and drain beef.
Add onion and pepper.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti "crust".
Top with tomato mixture, then Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix cheese into vegetables and soup.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top of mixture.
Pour melted margarine over mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: semsemia(sesame cookies)
directions: Brown sesame seeds slightly in the oven or on the stove top. Set aside.
Mix honey, peanut butter, sugar, rose water and cardamom in a saucepan.
Cook on low heat until it bubbles.
Stir in the sesame seeds and the walnuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 14-inch (or similar size) pan to cool.
To serve, cut in diamond shapes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour in bundt pan at 325°.

title: aunt jo's burgers italiano
directions: Start at 3:00 p.m.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place roast in oven and cook 1 hour.
Turn oven off.
Keep oven door closed! Forty-five minutes before serving, turn the oven to 300°.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Peel pears, halve and core with potato masher or food processor. Mash enough to make 1 cup pure. Cream butter, sugar, eggs and lemon rind until light. Mix flour, baking powder, salt and spices. Add pears and dry ingredients to creamed mixture, stirring until blended. Fold in nuts. Turn into greased and lightly floured ring mold (or you can use a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan). Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester inserted near center comes out clean. Let cake stand on wire rack for 5 minutes. Turn out of pan. Cool completely.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar and beat well.
Add milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Add nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°
and bake 20 minutes or until firm.
Test for doneness with a knife in center of pie.
If the knife comes out clean, the pie is done.

title: country-style coleslaw
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard and celery seed.
Stir well.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and toss well.
Chill.

title: mexican rice
directions: In large frying pan, heat oil on medium heat; add rice and brown.
Add tomato juice or sauce; heat about 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and bouillon, or base.
Pour in water.
Stir well; add onion and chili powder.

title: italian stuffed meat loaf
directions: Note:
Set aside additional 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1/8 cup sliced olives for garnish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as you do a cake with mashed bananas added last.
Bake in loaf pan 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: honey-soy drummettes
directions: In large baking dish, combine honey, apricot jam, soy sauce, ginger, mustard, chili sauce and hot pepper sauce. Mix well.
Add drummettes, turning to coat. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour to marinade. Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes in marinade; brush with marinade occasionally.

title: cracker barrel fried apples
directions: Peel apples and cut into wedges. Combine 2 cups of the apple juice and apples in skillet. Simmer and turn often until apples are done but not mushy. Remove apples with a slotted spoon to drain.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O and food coloring.
Pour over berries; chill.
Before serving, cover with whipped cream.

title: peek-a-boos
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Spoon a teaspoon of pie filling onto cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes or until golden and cake tests done (glass pan 325°). Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Spoon slightly sweetened whipped cream over each piece.
(Great served warm.)

title: quick mix fruit cocktail cake
directions: Heat oven to 375° (350° for glass).
Grease and flour an 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Combine quick bread mix, undrained fruit cocktail and egg; stir 60 to 75 strokes until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Combine nuts, chocolate chips and brown sugar; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool.

title: instant bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan, except cucumbers.
Bring to a boil and drop in 4 cups cucumbers.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Put into sterile jars and seal.
Makes about 2 pints.

title: pineapple and cream cheese salad
directions: Work enough grape juice into the cream cheese to soften. Make into balls with the hands or with butter paddle. Place a slice of pineapple on a lettuce leaf. Put a cheese ball on top and pour grape juice and French dressing over all.

title: hot slaw
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over low heat, stir together all the ingredients except cabbage. Add cabbage and mix well. Cover and simmer, stirring a few times, until tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: joseph's squash casserole
directions: Chop squash, tomatoes, onion and bell pepper into baking dish. Bake in oven at 350° until tender.
Add cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs; repeat.
Return to oven to melt cheese. Additional cheese may be added, if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans, bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until completely heated through.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Fry onion in butter until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except milk, crackers and eggs.
Boil gently for 30 minutes.
Add hot milk.
Let it boil up once.

title: beef tomato chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter; add beef and brown well.
Drain off excess grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes, or until serving time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: punch for 75
directions: This can be poured into quart cartons and frozen.
Thaw several hours before serving.
Add ginger ale right before serving.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: saucy barbecue shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp well and slit shell down back with paring knife. (Do not remove shell).
Combine all ingredients (except bread) in saucepan.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp to sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir 2 or 3 times. Bake shrimp in saucepan, uncovered at 300° turning twice until they just turn pink (about 15 to 18 minutes).
Do not overbake. Serve in generous soup bowls with chunks of French bread to soak up the sauce.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: hardtack candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until hard crack or 300°.
Add flavoring and coloring and pour out on confectioners sugar.
Roll into strings thin enough to cut with scissors.
Work quickly to prevent hardening.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream together.
Mix well.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or Pyrex dish, forming crust.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until slightly brown.
Cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put
all ingredients, except peanuts and baking soda on stove and
cook
until
real
brittle when dropped by spoon in cold water.
Pour
the
3 cups of shelled peanuts in and cook, stirring all
the time.
When syrup bubbles are turning brown take off stove
and add baking soda.
Stir real good and pour on big buttered
board
or
formica table top.
Pull from the edges as it	cools.	Keep pulling and breaking off in pieces. Keep doing this until all is pulled up.
This will keep a long time packed in Tupperware.

title: tasty taco salad
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet until browned. Stir until crumbled; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Cool slightly.
In a large bowl, layer half each of the tortilla chips, meat mixture, lettuce, cheese, kidney beans, tomatoes and onion.
Repeat layers.
Serve immediately with salad dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach fettucini
directions: Defrost spinach and drain in colander.
Cook noodles and drain.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Stir in spinach. Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup butter to warm noodles, tossing gently until butter melts.
Add spinach mixture, whipping cream and cheese. Toss gently and serve. Serves 6.
A great way to get kids to eat spinach!

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine in a 2-quart casserole and place in oven to melt margarine.
Pour macaroni into casserole with melted margarine.
Stir to coat macaroni with margarine. Sprinkle salt and pepper and shredded cheese through macaroni, toss lightly.
Pour milk over all.
Do not stir.
Do not cover while baking.
Cooking time:
1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.
Casserole size:
2 quarts.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs and water in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pan.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out and put Kisses on each.
Press down firmly.
Return to oven for 1 second.
Cool.

title: eggs with peppers
directions: Slice washed, pithed peppers lengthwise.
Heat oil in chafing dish.
Add peppers and sliced onions.
Saute 15 to 18 minutes, until peppers are soft.
Beat eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Fold in beaten eggs and cook for 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil and white sugar.
Add vanilla into eggs. Add this to first mixture, then sift flour, soda, cream of tartar, 10x sugar and salt.
Add with all the other ingredients.
Roll in small balls, then in some white sugar.
Press down with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium-size bowl; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate to chill.
Yield:
4 servings (1/2 cup each); lo-cal.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and
shortening.
Add milk and vinegar.
Roll out and put in pie pan.
Makes 2 pies.

title: zucchini "pizza" casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and sausage until brown and drain.
Add onion and seasonings.
Slice zucchini thinly; season this layer. Flip over the meat and onion mixture.
Slice more zucchini; season, turn and brown.
Add Cheddar cheese to cooked zucchini mixture; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Drizzle with spaghetti sauce and add more seasonings.
Turn heat down and cover until cheese melts. Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: pantry shelf chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to box; let cool.
Poke holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk and caramel on cake.
Top with Cool Whip and crunched up candy bars.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: While cake is baking, take same saucepan and melt margarine, milk and vanilla.
Remove from heat and pour in bowl with confectioners sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Pour on cake as soon as removed from oven.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown
the
pork
in
hot
shortening.
Stir
in water, chicken
bouillon cube and salt.
Cover;
simmer about 1 hour. Drain the pineapple, reserving the syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch
in
saucepan.
Add
reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add sauce to pork;
mix well.
Stir in pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, sift together flour, cocoa, cinnamon, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: applesauce raisin nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Add applesauce and raisins. Stir dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Fold in nuts. Bake in angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when stuck in cake.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar and corn syrup in 1 1/2-quart dish 7 to 8 minutes on High.
Stir well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and stir well.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Cool.
Break into chunks.
Store in airtight container.

title: wheat germ pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients from flour to cloves.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in pumpkin, then add blended dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and butterscotch bits.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet and bake according to directions.
Mix the sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: chewy chocolate chips
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together well. Add vinegar, vanilla and all dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Do not overbake if you like your cookies chewy.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Bring to boil 1 stick, Crisco, cocoa and cold water.
Pour over flour mix and stir.
Add buttermilk, cinnamon, salt, soda and eggs.
Stir and pour in pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
While brownies are baking, make Frosting.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie shell for 5 to 7 minutes. Distribute tuna, crab, shrimp or broccoli evenly on bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese and onion over tuna (etc.).
Beat eggs; add milk and mix; pour over tuna (etc.) mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 12 to 15 minutes more until top is golden.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon with apples slices.
Let stand.

title: pizza mix
directions: Mix, but don't beat.
Store in refrigerator.
Place on rounds or slice of bread.
Place under broiler until desired doneness.

title: cream cheese and almond tartlets
directions: Beat butter in large bowl of electric mixer until creamy.
Add cream cheese and beat again.
Blend in curry powder and hot pepper sauce.
Fill pastry shells with mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts. Makes 36 to 48 appetizers.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Pour into pan; place in refrigerator to chill.
Spread whip topping (8 ounces Cool Whip) over pudding.
Crush 5 Butterfinger candy bars; spread over whipped topping. Top with candy crumbs. Keep in refrigerator for several days or can be frozen.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat corn syrup. margarine and chocolate morsels just to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large mixing bowl.
Toss quickly until covered.
Fold in marshmallows one cup at a time.
Press evenly in pan with buttered back of a spoon.
Let stand until firm, at least 1 hour.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream shortening; slowly add sugar.
Cream well.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla, then add coconut.
Add flour mixture alternately with the milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Frost with seven minute frosting and cover with grated coconut.

title: date nut roll
directions: Melt the butter and marshmallows.
Add all the other ingredients and roll into about 6 to 8 rolls.
Keep cool in the refrigerator for easy slicing.
These make great gifts!

title: bavarian creme
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in the boiling water.
Add the cold water to which is added the reserved fruit juice to make up the 3/4 cup.
Chill until thickened.
Add the prepared Dream Whip or the whipped cream and then add the cup of drained fruit.
Mix until blended.
Pour into 1-quart mold or bowl and chill until firm.

title: spinach broccoli casserole
directions: Cook together until tender and drain well.
Mix onion soup mix and 1 pint of sour cream.
Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Heat for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Place grated cheese (Cheddar on top just until melted).
Serves 8.

title: crab rangoon(makes 60)
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, Parmesan, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and sugar; mix well.
Add onions and crab meat; mix well.
In small bowl, beat egg with water.

title: a nice indian pudding
directions: Stir meat and milk together while hot.
Let stand until cooled.
Add raisins, butter, eggs, spice and sugar.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon barbecued pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chops in an ungreased pan.
Season and top with the onion, lemon and catsup.
Cover lightly with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: dawn's breakfast casserole
directions: Spray bottom of pan with Pam.
Layer ingredients in order given in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Put jelly and cocktail sauce in crock or pan; heat together. Use the rest of the ingredients to make meatballs.
Simmer meatballs and sauce, uncovered, for about 30 minutes, or until balls float (which indicates that they're done).
Serve hot.

title: mountain dew apple cobbler
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 16 sections. Wrap each piece of apple in a crescent roll, sealing seams and edges. Place in a 13 x 9 pan. Melt butter and mix with sugar. Spoon over apples. Pour Mountain Dew over that. Sprinkle with cinnamon and pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey
directions: Wash turkey well.
Rub turkey with oleo, then add salt and pepper.
Place in large roaster with sufficient water to make gravy if desired.
Bake in a 300° oven allowing approximately 30 minutes per pound.
Reserve juice for gravy and dressing.

title: all in one steak meal
directions: Wrap in foil. Cook approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375° until tender.

title: savory chicken breasts
directions: Place breasts in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and milk. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over evenly.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffing.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; bake an additional 20 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: You will need tender mild yellow, very sweet ears, slightly younger than table ready.

title: butter stick biscuits
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl with a fork.
Spread in pan with butter on bottom.
Cut squares with sharp knife before baking.
Bread will lift out when done.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread and sausage pie
directions: Follow directions on package of muffin mix; add sausage .
Pour in greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush Oreos.
Mix margarine with Oreos and put in the bottom of pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs in medium bowl.
Add other ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half mixture in 9-inch pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle cheese, then add the rest of the mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Divide into 6 servings.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over rolls. Use second can of rolls for top crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar icing.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
In medium bowl, cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed 2 minutes after each addition.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla. Spoon into cooled pie shell.
Chill 2 hours or until served. Serve with whipped cream and nuts.
Makes 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: pickled okra
directions: Add garlic, alum, dill seed and peppers to each pint of okra used.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together butter, flour and nuts and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool.

title: sweet disposition recipe
directions: Do not bring to a boil, please!

title: melt in your mouth sausage
directions: Place sausage in skillet. Cover with water and simmer 10 minutes. Drain. Combine remaining ingredients in slow cooker and add sausage. Cover and cook on low 6 hours. Serve in buns or over cooked spaghetti.

title: gelatine yogurt pie
directions: Beat egg yolk and gelatin together.
Add boiling water, stir until dissolved.
Add milk and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Whip egg whites until soft peaks form;
and fold in yogurt and gelatin.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover and chill until set.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave or at room temperature.
Chop all of green onions in 1/4 to 3/8-inch size.
Cut or tear dried beef into small pieces.
Mix all together in small bowl, using table fork.
Add garlic salt to taste.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spray paper grocery bag with Pam.
Add popcorn.
Put rest of ingredients, except baking soda, in glass dish; no need to mix. Microwave on High until it starts to boil.
Mix a little.
Let boil 2 minutes.
Add the baking soda; stir well.
Pour mixture over popcorn in bag.
Roll top of bag down; shake hard.
Put bag in microwave on High for 30 seconds (15 to 20 seconds for half recipe).
Take out; shake bag hard.
Put back on High for 1 1/2 minutes (45 seconds for 1/2 recipe).
Shake again for 30 seconds. Pour onto cookie sheets.

title: quick chicken fricassee
directions: Take chicken breasts and place skin side down in a shallow casserole.
Cover with condensed cream of chicken soup.
Put in oven 1/2 hour at 325°.
After 1/2 hour, turn over and cook 1/2 hour more.
You can add a few drops of sherry.
Eat with rice, pasta, etc.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with cheese slices.
Blanch vegetables.
Put over cheese slices.
Crush Ritz crackers to cover top.
Pour butter over crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Add oleo to crumbs. Pack 2/3 of crumbs into and on sides of a 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top of filling.

title: "no fat strawberry shake"
directions: Freeze the strawberries ahead, then add berries in blender and blend on liquefy for 30 to 45 seconds in an electric blender. Makes 2 shakes.

title: brunch puff
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cut crusts off of bread.
Spread 6 slices in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of bacon and half of cheese.
Repeat layer.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top layer in pan.
This may be covered and refrigerated overnight before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
It should be set and puffed.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion. Pour 1/4 cup sauce on bottom of casserole. Place tortillas on bottom of casserole. Layer kidney beans, hamburger and cheese. Pour 1/4 cup sauce over layers. Repeat until all ingredients are used. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish:
cooked broccoli, chips, sliced eggs and cheese; repeat layers.
Top with cream of mushroom soup thinned with a little milk.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake for 3 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar taken from the 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Place shortening and remaining sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add 2 cups boiling water. Mix well and cool to lukewarm.
Beat in eggs and yeast.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the flour to make a soft dough; gradually add remaining flour.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and put a plate over the wrap.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Push down, then refrigerate overnight.
Push down again in the morning.
Roll and cut into fold-over rolls.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in hot oven.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and ice cream with electric mixer.
Stir in dairy topping.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.
Garnish with peanuts, serve with hot fudge sauce.

title: golden carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans. Beat at medium speed until thoroughly blended. Pour evenly into greased oblong cake pan (9x13 inch). Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done at 350 degrees. Remove from oven. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Brush warm cake with glaze until all glaze is used.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix the flour, sugar, apple juice and egg. Cook over low heat until thick.
Refrigerate sauce until cool. Add Cool Whip, apples, pineapple and 1/2 cup nuts.

title: mrs. simons lemon chess pie
directions: Start eggs beating; add 1 cup sugar.
Mix 1 cup sugar with cornmeal and flour.
Add to eggs and sugar.
Add last 5 ingredients.
Pour into large unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400°, then turn oven to 325° and bake until firm and nice brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cut top from one round loaf of rye or pumpernickel bread.
Remove
soft
insides for dipping.
Place on serving plate.
Place
bread scraps around loaf.
Fill loaf with filling.
Sit
back
and
receive your compliments.
Very good to serve at parties.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Pour into a well greased 10-inch skillet.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Melt butter; add minced onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir to blend well.
Add milk and stir over low heat.
Add sauce, tuna and 1/2 cheese to noodles.
Stir gently.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked apple butter
directions: Heat oven to 275-300°. Mix ingredients; cook in oven until thick. Stir about every half hour. Pour into hot sterilized jars. Makes 5 pints.

title: chocolate toffee caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9 pan. In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs. Blend well. Stir in chocolate chips, white vanilla chips and candy bar pieces (mixture will be thick). Press half of mixture in bottom of greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Place 18 frozen bread balls in greased Bundt pan.
(Do not use angel food cake pan!)
Drizzle melted margarine over frozen dough. Combine dry ingredients.
Sprinkle over frozen dough.
Let sit overnight at room temperature.
In the morning, bake coffee cake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and after a minute or so, invert onto large plate.
Lots of gooey caramel!!

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in cup of boiling water.
Let cool until syrupy.
Mix in other ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: louise's scrumptious peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a large, heavy frying pan.
Place over medium heat and stir until sugar dissolves. Cover and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove cover and cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Add peanuts.
Stirring frequently, cook until brittle reaches hard crack or brittle stage (300°).
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Baking soda will make mixture foamy.
Stir until blended but mixture must still be foamy. Spread on a well-buttered, 14 1/2 x 17-inch cookie sheet.

title: ozark pudding pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in apple, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: coconut pies(yields 2)
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar with eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix milk and flavoring with other ingredients.
Add coconut and butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When thick, pour into prepared crusts.
Top with meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut. Brown slightly.

title: peanut butterfinger chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
In a mixer, blend sugars, butter, egg whites and vanilla until fluffy, about 1 minute at high speed.
Add peanut butter and beat until well mixed.
At low speed, add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped Butterfingers.
Mound dough on cookie sheets about 2 inches apart.
Use 1 1/2 tablespoons for larger cookies or 1 tablespoon for smaller.
Bake about 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the size made.
Cool on sheets for 3 minutes and then remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen large or 6 dozen small cookies.

title: betty crocker's poppy seed muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fill halfway in cupcake pan (lined or greased).
Heat oven to 325°.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in 4 cups boiling water.
Add sugar to the other 4 cups water;
bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O mixture; set aside to cool.
Add lemon and pineapple juice.
Pour into plastic containers and freeze.
When ready to use, put frozen juice in bowl; add ginger ale.
Serves 30 to 40.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients and add vegetables of choice. Refrigerate and toss frequently.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Make cake by directions on box, adding 1 cup strawberries and flavoring.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Line cupcake pans with baking cups. Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each baking cup in pans.
Pour cheese mixture on top.
Add cherry filling.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Chill before serving.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Easy, but oh so good.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake in baking dish at 350° until thick and brown.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt chocolate bar in 6 ounces chocolate syrup over very low heat.
Add remaining syrup, stirring to be sure all candy is dissolved and smooth.
Set aside to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs (1 at a time), beating after each.
Add syrup mixture (it should be cool).
Add flour and buttermilk (with soda dissolved in it) alternately.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 325° (tube cake pan) one hour depending upon oven; some may take longer.
Just insert toothpick to be sure of doneness.
No icing necessary.
This cake freezes very well.

title: blueberry vinegar
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; simmer 10 minutes. Place in a large screw-top jar; store for 3 weeks away from direct sunlight.
Strain mixture to separate vinegar from berries, pressing berries with a spoon to get all the juice out.
Strain once more through a coffee filter.
Pour into a clean, dry decorative bottle.
We do not recommend adding fresh berries to the finished product.
Rapid deterioration of the fruit can cause cloudiness and sediment to form.
Use within 3 months.

title: pink salad
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple tidbits (drained), frozen strawberries, bananas and a little red coloring.
Mix very well.
Freeze overnight.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add 3 eggs and one teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Start in cold oven and cook 10 minutes at 350°, then turn oven temperature to 300° and cook until done.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple juice into measuring cup.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Bring to boil pineapple, water and oleo.
Stir cornstarch in 1/4 cup of cold water, then pour in and stir until pineapple are thick.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with other crust. Slit holes in top to let steam escape.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown in 350° oven.
Cool before cutting.

title: cooked pimento mix
directions: Remove seeds and grind peppers; drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients; add peppers.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Use with mayonnaise and Velveeta or finely grated mild Cheddar cheese for the best pimento cheese sandwiches ever.

title: lasagne
directions: Cut casings from Italian sausage and brown, drain well.
Boil Lasagne noodles 15 minutes and drain.
Mix sauce:
paste, stewed tomatoes, puree, parsley, Italian seasoning, garlic powder and add Italian sausage.
Set aside.
Arrange in layers in greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan (sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, sauce, noodles, mozzarella cheese etc.
End with noodles on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Do not add water.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir as you add each ingredient.
Don't drain corn.
Melt oleo in pan you are baking in.
Add corn, onion, pepper and corn meal. Fold in sour cream.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: dutch bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs and add white sugar and brown sugar.
Beat well.
Next, add oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk to eggs and sugar. Add raisins and nuts. Bake in four 1 pound coffee cans that have been sprayed with nonstick Pam.
Cook for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool 20 minutes and remove.
Makes 4 beautiful round coffee cakes. Each slice is round and moist. Freezes well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring oil, pepper, sugar, vinegar, salt and water to a boil for 1 minute.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.

title: glorified fruit
directions: Mix all fruit and nuts together and pour fruit pie filling over mixture.
Refrigerate after stirring together and serve. Good and easy.

title: lemon bisque dessert
directions: Chill can of milk in refrigerator.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add honey, salt, lemon juice and rind.
When slightly thick, beat milk until it is stiff and whip gelatin mixture over it.
Put on vanilla wafer crumbs, top with more crumbs and chill for 3 hours.
Also like it frozen and slightly thawed.

title: munching peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir together and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until it browns.
Add vanilla and butter to syrup.
Blend well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup will be very hot.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Quickly put mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 30 to 60 minutes.
When cool, break into tiny pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large pan, saute bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
In same skillet, saute onion and potato.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add all clam juice; stir and bring to boil.
Simmer until potatoes are soft, about 15 minutes.
Add half and half. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add minced clams; heat until simmering.
Don't boil.
Add whipping cream.
Sprinkle with diced bacon.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken,
remove
bones
and
cut in small pieces. Add butter to
chicken
broth,
then
add dressing mix.
Place chicken in a
casserole
dish and spoon dressing over chicken. Mix together soup and water and pour over chicken and dressing mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in one bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Will keep for one week.

title: oreo-ice cream cake
directions: Crumble 1 package Oreo cookies and spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Save some for topping.)
Heat one can of Hershey's hot fudge and spread over cookies.
Cool completely.
Soften ice cream and spread over cooled cookie mixture.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip, remaining cookie crumbs and nuts, if desired.
Freeze before serving.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars.
Add both eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and combine with first mixture.
Add oatmeal, nuts or raisins.
Dough is very stiff.
Make into 2 rolls and wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice and bake at 350° until brown.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Sprinkle generously with kindness.
Add plenty of faith and mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime.
Serve everyone you meet.

title: pepperoni(10 pounds)
directions: Mix all together.
Form into rolls, 2 1/2 inches in diameter. Wrap in heavy foil or double thickness regular foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake on broiler pan at 300° for 2 hours; cool before slicing.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator or can be frozen.
