title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together margarine, graham cracker crumbs, sugar and peanut butter.
Press in 13 x 9 inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate morsels and spread over the top.
Let harden.
Cut into squares.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: texas caviar or oklahoma caviar(two recipes for black-eyed peas)
directions: Mix black-eyed peas, green pepper, onion, jalapeno pepper, salad dressing and tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chinese crab salad
directions: Combine and add just enough mayo to moisten.
Optional: Drizzle 1 or 2 tablespoons lemon juice over crab 15 minutes before mixing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour Italian dressing over all and refrigerate.

title: classic french vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Peel garlic, slice thinly and then sprinkle with a little salt.
Smash to a pulp with a knife.
Place in a bowl and add mustard and sugar. Stir well.
Add pepper, wine vinegar and olive oil.
Stir well.

title: biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, cream of tartar and salt and cut in shortening.
It will resemble coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center and add milk at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently for 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in pressure cooker for 10 minutes.
Let cool, then pick into small pieces.
Put in bottom layer of pan.
Mix soups, celery and onion.
Put on top of stove and heat.
Pour over chicken.
Put a layer of stuffing over chicken.
Pour broth from chicken over dressing and punch holes to allow it to saturate.

title: squash bake
directions: Boil squash until tender, then mash.
Saute onion tops and bottoms.
Crumble bacon and mix with squash, onions, salt and pepper to taste and add evaporated milk.
Turn into baking dish. Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 300° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: claudia's green chili enchiladas
directions: Heat
enchilada
sauce, water (enough to rinse can) and juice from
green chilies in a saucepan (big enough to hold a flat tortilla).	Meanwhile, fry meat and pour grease off.
Add garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper to meat.
Get remaining ingredients ready and grease large ovenware dish.
Dip tortillas
in 1/4-inch of hot oil.
Fry quickly on both sides (don't let
it get crisp). Put in sauce.
Place on serving dish.
In middle
of
tortilla, place
meat,
cheese,
onion
and green chilies.
Roll
the tortilla
and
place
the
end on bottom. Cover with remaining sauce, cheese and green chilies.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes or microwave.

title: new york lemon cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust for 9-inch nonstick spring-form pan.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 to cream mixture.
Add finely crumbled mincemeat and water and stir until blended.
Add nuts and remaining flour mixture.
Mix well.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: muffins
directions: Add sugar to mix.
Combine milk and egg; stir into mix until flour is just moistened.
Add fruit, if desired.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry bread with strawberry cream cheese
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients. Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool.
Makes 16 servings.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put rhubarb, 3 tablespoons flour and 1 cup sugar in a 2-quart baking dish.
Blend 1 1/2 cups flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and margarine.
Sprinkle topping over rhubarb mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding eggs and oil last.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain fruit; reserve juice.
Add enough 7-Up to juice to make 3 cups of liquid.
Add cream cheese and dissolve it.
Add mayonnaise, nuts and pineapple.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread this over crust.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat until thickened.
Spread pudding on top of cream cheese layer.
Spread more Cool Whip on top and sprinkle chopped nuts and crushed Skor bar over all.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna teaser
directions: Combine soup and milk in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Fold in tuna, macaroni and peas.
Sprinkle crushed chips on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter, then add cream cheese.
Add salts and chopped green chilies and mix well.
Add corn.
This is better served hot.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add vanilla wafers and milk; mix well.
Add coconut and pecans; bake in tub pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creole liver
directions: Dice bacon, fry until crisp and remove from fat.
Dredge liver with flour and brown in bacon fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bacon.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti.
Serves 5.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt tomato soup, gelatin
and
cream
cheese in top of double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, celery and shrimp cut in bite
size
pieces.
Pour into mold greased with mayonnaise. Chill overnight.
Unmold and serve with a variety of crackers.

title: cucumbers 'n cream
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and chill for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Combine drained cucumbers with onion and sour cream.
Can be served in individual bowls and garnished with tomato wedges, if desired.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, using milk instead of water. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes with large fork in cake.
Heat pineapple and sugar to just boiling. Pour into cake, let cool.
Mix pudding according to directions. Blend in cream cheese.
Spread this mixture on cake.
Refrigerate until set.
Slice 3 to 4 bananas on top of pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped pecans.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Rhubarb goes in last.

title: white nut bread
directions: Mix together thoroughly the sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together and stir in the flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes (until wooden toothpick thrust into center comes out clean).
Serve warm or cold.
Cut with thin sharp knife to prevent crumbling.

title: strawberry upside-down biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Grease 10 muffin cups generously. Place 1 tablespoon of preserves in each cup.
Cover with a biscuit and bake.
Turn out upside down immediately.

title: easy layer bake
directions: Cook
noodles.	Stir
together	the
cream cheese, sour cream and
milk.	In
a
2 quart casserole, layer half of the meat mixture,
all
of
the spinach and half the cream cheese mixture. Add
the
remainder
of the meat and the rest of the cream	cheese mixture.
Top with grated cheese.	Bake at 350° for 40
to
50 minutes.
This
can be fixed ahead of time and frozen.

title: mama's yeast bread
directions: Mix all together.
Add yeast with flour to make a stiff dough. Let rise double in size.
Make 2 pieces on floured wax paper. Let rise for 15 minutes.
Make 2 loaves in greased pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix water, Jell-O, crushed pineapple and blueberries.
Let chill.
Mix other ingredients and spread over congealed Jell-O mixture.
Serve.

title: sour cream pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with the rolled-out dough; prick all over with a fork, then press a piece of heavy-duty foil directly into the pie shell.
Bake for 6 minutes; remove the foil and bake for about 4 more minutes.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Beat the pumpkin and eggs together in a large bowl, then stir in the sour cream, milk and sugar.
Add the salt and spices and beat until smooth.
Pour the filling into the pie shell and bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue to bake for 30 to 40 minutes until filling is almost firm.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: lasagne
directions: Add to the browned and drained hamburger, the onion, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano leaves.
Stir and cook for 20 minutes or so, then add the tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Let this cook on low for as long as you have time.
I usually let cook for 1 to 2 hours.
Keep stirred.
Make layers.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and molasses. Combine dry ingredients and add to other ingredients.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in greased cookie pan.
Drop by round spoonful onto cookie sheet.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Roll lemon to soften; cut in half, and squeeze out juice.
Add lemon juice to fruit syrup.
Cut apples, oranges, grapes, and strawberries into bite-sized pieces.
Make melon balls from the cantaloupe.
Arrange fruit in bowl.
Pour syrup over fruit. Serve.

title: butter crunch
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients with hands.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes; stir with spoon.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: eskimo bread
directions: Place flour, pancake mix, salt, egg, baking powder and oil in large mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 of milk.
Add brown sugar to remainder of milk until medium brown color.
Add milk and sugar mixture to mixing bowl.
Take approximately 2 tablespoons warm water and rinse out cup which held sugar and milk mixture.
Add this water to bowl.
Gradually stir flour into side of bowl that holds the liquid.
Mix until all flour is mixed in.
Batter will be thick and sticky.
Heat skillet with hot Crisco oil.
Drop dough into hot oil by large tablespoonfuls.
Flatten dough out with spatula so it cooks thoroughly.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen pieces of bread.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Dice onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery.
Saute in butter (1 stick).
Combine spaghetti and sauteed vegetables in a 4-quart baking dish.
Stir in soups.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Add chicken.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle with chili pepper.
Can also add sliced green olives, if desired.
Heat 25 minutes at 325°, until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add extracts.
Combine flour and salt to egg mixture. Alternate with milk, ending with flour.
Cook in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cake cool for 10 minutes in pan.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Mix all ingredients together and rub on leg of lamb.
Allow to sit in refrigerator overnight.
Pour 1/2 cup dry white wine and 1/2 cup water (or 4 tablespoons lemon juice and 3/4 cup water) into shallow roasting pan.
Place lamb in pan and roast at 275° for approximately 25 minutes per pound, until thermometer reads 160°.
(Six-pound roast takes about 2 1/2 hours.)

title: soft drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together except sugar.
Set aside.
Cream the shortening (butter) and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Add vanilla. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy punch
directions: Place frozen pineapple juice cubes in punch bowl.
Pour soda over.
Adjust amount, depending on how much punch you need.

title: chocolate almond cakes
directions: Grease three 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch pans.
Line with wax paper and grease the paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: lemon sticks
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar, lemon juice and nuts. Spread over baked mixture and bake 25 minutes longer. Cut when cool.

title: tom's "famous" peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside. Cream the Crisco, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by large spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: tuna on a shoestring
directions: In a bowl, mix carrots, celery, onion, tuna and mayonnaise. Just before serving, add shoestring potatoes.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Mix in saucepan.
First, melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar and oatmeal; stir and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Break egg into mixture.
Add salt, coconut and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: ice cream (any flavor)
directions: Mix all ingredients and
pour
into freezer.
Add whole milk and fill to 3 inches of top of can.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: midwestern lemon pudding
directions: In small bowl, beat egg yolks with milk, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold yolk mixture into the whites.
Butter a 1-quart deep casserole.
Pour mixture into the casserole.
Place into a larger pan in oven.
Pour hot water into the pan to a 1-inch depth.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm or cooled, garnished with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: my grandmother's dark fruit cake
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes with mixer the oil, brown sugar and egg yolks.
Sift spices, salt, baking powder and 2 cups of flour.
Add a little flour mixture to the first mixture alternately with fruit juice.
Add fruit and nuts, mixed with remaining 1 cup of flour. Fold in beaten egg whites that have been beaten stiff.
Bake in a tube pan real slow at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
I keep a pan of water on the shelf below in the oven.
This keeps it moist.

title: strawberry-orange summer cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch round cake pan.
In small bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In a small mixer bowl beat eggs 5 minutes at medium speed until thick and light yellow colored.
Gradually beat in 3/4 cup sugar.
Continue beating 2 minutes.
On low speed, beat in orange peel, juice and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture, beating just until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides and remove from pan and cool.
Slice berries into medium mixing bowl.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Whip cream until soft peaks form.
Stir yogurt in carton until smooth.
Fold into whipping cream.
Cut cake in half horizontally.
Place bottom half on serving plate.
Spoon 2/3 of the sliced berries and juice over cake.
Spoon 1/2 of the whipped cream mixture over berries. Place second cake layer on top of cream.
Spooning remaining berries, and juice and then whipped cream mixture over cake.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Spray loaf pan or glass dish.
Mix all ingredients together and place in pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with the water, then mix in the egg yolks.
Pour into boiling milk mixture.
Whisk until thick.
Remove from heat and whisk in peanut butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: rocky mount cake
directions: Grind raisins, coconut and walnuts up fine (food chopper). Make cake layers out of cake mix.
Mix milk, sugar, vanilla and butter.
Put in pot and let come to a rolling boil.
Add raisins, coconut and walnuts.
Stir well and put on cake layers.

title: 5 minute chicken and rice
directions: You can throw this together in 5 minutes!

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute in oil the onion and jalapeno pepper.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, beef broth, sugar, chicken broth, cumin, tomato soup, Tabasco sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add corn tortillas, cut in pieces; simmer 5 minutes.
Chop 4 or 5 avocados.
Put in bowls and then add hot soup.

title: quick breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch dish with the crescent rolls, sealing perforations. Cover with sausage, mushrooms and half the cheese. Mix the eggs with soup and pour over casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving size pieces.
In large saucepan, cover ribs with salted water.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.

title: debbie jackman's cheese cake(just 3 ingredients)
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly with electric hand beater.
Put into graham cracker crust.

title: shrimp luncheon sandwiches
directions: Blend cheese with mayonnaise.
Mix in ketchup, mustard and garlic powder.
Stir in shrimp, celery and onion.
Use as a filling between slices of sandwich bread.
Trim crusts, if desired.
Cut each sandwich diagonally into 4 triangles.
Makes about 20 tea sandwiches.
May be used as a dip.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer.
Blend in melted, cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating 5 minutes or longer.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Press ground beef into bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with canned milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Slice potatoes on meat.
Slice onions.
Cube cheese onto the potatoes and onions.
Layer again if you like.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 6 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
You may want to add sugar and/or dressing to taste.
Sprinkle in shredded carrots for color.
Use over sliced cucumbers.
Recipe is easily halved.

title: delma's pineapple ginger ale cooler
directions: Place 1 tablespoon pineapple in each of two 4 ounce glasses. Pour ginger ale over pineapple.
Top with spoonful whipped topping.
Sip with straw.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture of oil, garlic, red pepper, sherry, ginger, ketchup and sugar over night.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 6 to 10 minutes on each side at 425 degrees; basting often with teriyaki sauce.

title: buckeyes (cookies)
directions: Blend first four ingredients in mixer until looks like dough. Work together with hands and make balls size of walnuts.

title: chicken vegetable medley
directions: Combine chicken, chicken soup and spices and let sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in skillet with water and cook until the chicken is browned.
Add vegetables and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato slices 5 minutes before serving.

title: pecan sticky buns
directions: In bowl, combine sugar, pecans, cinnamon and melted butter. Cut biscuits in quarters.
In Bundt pan, layer pecan mixture, biscuits and so forth until completed.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. When completed, let cook for 5 minutes then turn onto plate.

title: w b a q's own pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer.
Grease and flour four (1 pound) coffee cans. Fill half full with mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Remove from oven and let cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from cans and wrap in plastic.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey and onion in a large heavy pot, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, water, tomatoes, tomato paste and chili powder.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with crackers or French bread.
Great on a cold snowy night!

title: hershey pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and soda with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and candy bars which have been melted in a double boiler.
Bake in stem pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand in pan until cool.
(Two loaf pans may be used instead of stem pan.)

title: crab salad
directions: Blend all of the ingredients.
Chill in the refrigerator. Enjoy!

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; bring to hard boil. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Beat well, then add the oatmeal and nuts. Stir until thickened. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Helpful Hint:
Soften cream cheese in microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds.

title: country fried steak
directions: Roll steak in flour; brown on each side in hot oil.
Add hot water and onion.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve.
Yields 5 servings.

title: two tone rolls
directions: Thaw both loaves of bread.
Cut each one in half crosswise. Roll piece of white dough into 8 x 6-inch rectangle on lightly floured surface.
Set off to one side.
Roll 1 piece of wheat dough into 8 x 6-inch rectangle.

title: joe's peanut brittle
directions: Mix and cook sugar, water and Karo in heavy pan until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Add peanuts and salt, cook until brown.
Stir in butter and soda quickly and pour on buttered foil.

title: cream cheese cherry pie(fast and easy)
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften for best results.

title: polish love knots
directions: Add salt to eggs; beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and flavoring; continue to beat.
Add sour cream and flour alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Knead on floured board until dough blisters.
Cut in halves.
Roll very thin; cut into strips about 4 inches long.
Slit each piece in center and pull through slit.
Fry in fat until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: luscious chicken
directions: Combine pancake flour, milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Dip chicken in mixture, then in flour.
Deep fry until golden brown. Easy and luscious.

title: green chili pie
directions: Butter a casserole dish. Drain chillies and place in bottom of dish. Cover with cheese. Mix eggs, milk and tabasco sauce. Pour over all ingredients. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: mint molds
directions: *If using other flavors, it will be necessary to use 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter over low heat; remove from heat and mix in brown sugar. Cool.
Stir in egg.
Mix together dry ingredients and stir into brown sugar mixture.
Blend in vanilla, nuts and chips.

title: apple pie(baked in a paper sack)
directions: Cut up
apples.
Mix
cup
sugar and 2 tablespoons flour; mix
with
apples.
Sprinkle
with cinnamon.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Mix
1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour; pour over top of apples.
Slice
butter
on
top of flour mixture. Place in a large paper sack, clip ends loosely and bake 1 hour at 425°.

title: dressing for tossed salad
directions: Grate onion; set aside.
Use a quart jar for mixing.
Add salt, dry mustard, sugar and vinegar.
Shake well.
Add onion and Wesson oil.
Shake again well.
It's ready to use and will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil
chicken
covered
in
water until tender.
Remove skin and
bones and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Add 1/2 to chicken.
Grate cheeses together.
Add half
to chicken.
Add
remaining ingredients to chicken mixture.
Heat flour
tortilla in hot skillet and spoon on about 1/4
cup filling.
Roll up.
Place, seam side down, in greased 9 x 13-inch baking
dish.
Top tortillas with remaining soup-sour
cream mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Put remaining cheese on top and return to oven to melt.
Makes 10.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook over low heat until boiling. Stir. Remove from heat and pour over peanut butter mixture* in deep dish pie shell.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Heat cream cheese and soup in microwave until cream cheese is melted.
Pour meat in a casserole dish; next, pour the soup mixture and spread over meat. Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Place biscuits on top of cheese and bake until biscuits are brown at 350°, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine undiluted milk, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate bits and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Cool and cut.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer veggies in order given in crock-pot with salt and pepper.
Place lightly browned beef over top.
Mix soup and water; pour over all.
Cook on slow for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 2 to 4 hours.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and marinate in 1/2 cup Lawry's citrus grill with orange juice for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Put seasoned bread crumbs in bag and add chicken and coat.
Cook in skillet in oil over medium heat.

title: finnish turnip casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add melted butter, farina, eggs, milk, sugar and spices to mashed turnip.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Dot with the 2 tablespoons cut up butter and bake at least 1 hour or a little longer until top is browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In saucepan, melt margarine; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in 1 cup shredded cheese until melted.
Combine macaroni and cheese sauce.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For larger meals, double the recipe.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender; drain.
Add other ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup crumbs and a small amount of butter for top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into shortening mixture.
Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts; roll in the mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
The cookies puff up a little, then flatten a little when they come out of the oven.
Don't overbake or they may get a little hard.
Makes about 3 dozen, unless making real small balls, then makes more.

title: crab puffs
directions: Tip:
May use clam, salmon or shrimp instead of crab!

title: capital punishment chili
directions: Brown all meat in a large skillet until fat is cooked off. Transfer meat to an 8-quart stockpot.
Saute onions and garlic in skillet until tender; add to meat and mix well.
Add liquids and spices and simmer.
If you like beans in your chili, add them to mixture 1/2 hour before it's ready to eat.
As for cooking time, give it a couple of hours, then taste.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to directions.
When cool, crumble half of baked cornbread into a large bowl.
In another bowl, combine next 5 ingredients.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture over cornbread.
Stir together mayo and pickle juice.
Spread 1/2 of this over vegetable layer.
Repeat layering with remaining cornbread, veggies and dressing.
Cover tightly; chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put fresh grease in kettle. When grease is hot, fill funnel with flour mixture.
Allow mixture to drizzle into hot greased until desired size.
(Place finger on funnel tip to prevent more mixture from dripping out.)
Fry until golden brown.
Lift out and drain.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: potluck pot roast
directions: Bake chuck roast in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Then cut up celery, onions, potatoes and carrots.
Place around roast.
Add a teaspoon of salt, dash of pepper and seasoning.
Bake for another 1 1/2 hours until tender.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: (French onion soup works too.)

title: crab mold appetizer
directions: Warm mushroom soup and cream cheese together in medium pan. Add gelatine dissolved in water.
Add celery, onions, mayonnaise and crab.
Fill mold and refrigerate until set.

title: peanut butter and jelly loaf(two 8 x 4-inch loaves)
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and sugars.
Beat in peanut butter and milk.
Combine and add dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Spread batter in prepared 8 x 4-inch pans (2).
Drop jam by tablespoons on top.
Swirl jam into batter lightly using a knife. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until loaves test done.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix well with spoon.
Bake in muffin pan until done at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Use enough evaporated milk to mix ingredients into a moist loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chili dip
directions: In a small casserole dish, spread cream cheese to cover the bottom of the pan.
Top with chili, then sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake or microwave until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Best if made a day before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Pour into pie plate and bake at 350° until starts to firm up. Do not overbake.

title: glazed carrot packet
directions: You will need 1 sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil (18 x 24-inches).

title: s'more tarts
directions: Prepare brownie batter according to package directions. Place graham cracker shells on a baking sheet and fill with brownie batter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out with moist crumbs. Immediately sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips. Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer or until marshmallows are puffed and golden brown. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: buttermilk cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray two loaf pans, or 5 mini-loaf pans, with cooking spray and set aside. Combine cinnamon and 1 cup sugar; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, and salt; set aside. In a small bowl, combine oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Add buttermilk and eggs; mix well. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill the two loaf pans about 1/3 full with the batter. Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the cinnamon-sugar over each pan of batter. Top with remaining batter and cinnamon-sugar. Swirl batter with a knife. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.

title: mama's old time syrup pie
directions: In a saucepan, let
syrup
come
to a boil. Add butter. Beat eggs in bowl until fluffy.	Mix together sugar and flour; add to eggs.
Mix well and add these ingredients to the syrup. Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° to 350° or until mixture is set.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Grease and flour fluted Bundt pan.
Set oven to 350°.
Mix altogether; bake 55 minutes or more until cake springs back on top.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: layered salad
directions: Prepare the day ahead and layer in order given.
Real good.

title: cammie's potato pancakes
directions: Grate the potatoes and onion in a large bowl.
Add egg and flour.
Mix to a semi-thick mixture (more flour can be added). Stir in salt and sugar.
Have pan ready with vegetable oil.
Let oil get hot. Scoop batter with large spoon and drop in pan (size for pancakes).
Fry until golden brown.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until blended well.
Cook noodles.
Mix all together and bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients; bring to boil and pour over the dry ingredients (flour, sugar, soda and salt). Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in sheet pan at 350°.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except yeast. When thoroughly mixed, add yeast and knead dough. Place into a greased bowl; cover and let rest 20 minutes. Divide into 24 small balls. Place 3 balls together in greased muffin cups. Cover and let rise until almost doubled (30 to 50 minutes). Brush rolls with beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove and serve warm. Makes 8 rolls. May double recipe.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown beef until crumbly.
Drain.
Mix in A.1. and spaghetti sauce.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with sauce.
Layer lasagna noodles (uncooked), cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Repeat.
End with lasagna, sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Allow to stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, margarine, vanilla and cinnamon in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in milk.
Pour cream cheese mixture over combined bread and cranberries in large bowl; toss lightly.
Let stand 15 minutes, rearranging bread in bowl occasionally to moisten evenly.
Arrange bread in rows in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining cream cheese mixture over bread.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with Cranberry Maple Sauce.

title: beginner biscuits
directions: Mix flour and melted grease with milk until thick.
Spoon them into a greased pan.
Bake at 450° until browned.
Makes 5 biscuits.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onion, pepper or celery together in bowl.
Mix together sugar, vinegar and salad oil and pour over bean mixture. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Partially melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from hot water and stir rapidly until entirely melted.
Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavorings and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to shortening and mix well.
Stir in chocolate until blended.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan.
While still hot, place under tightly fitting cover until thoroughly cooled.
Tastes great with or without glaze.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Blend cocoa into melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into pie shells.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
Freezes well.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt oleo and add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir well.
Add oatmeal and mix completely.
Spoon out on waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugar and cocoa. Add eggs, flour, salt, soda, milk, baking powder and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: homemade herb mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in tight jar.
Stir or shake before using.

title: shipwreck
directions: In a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan, put a layer of ground beef (not browned), then a layer of thinly sliced potatoes, followed by a layer of thinly sliced onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with a can of kidney beans.
Add another layer of ground beef.
Top with a can of tomato soup (straight from the can, not weakened) and spread out on ground beef.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 4 hours.

title: champagne punch
directions: Put orange juice in punch
bowl and add water; mix well.
Add club soda and champagne.
Float orange sherbet.

title: play dough
directions: Pour boiling water over other ingredients.
Add food coloring. Knead to desired consistency.
Keep in covered container.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Press into ungreased pan (13 x 9-inch). Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel
and
cut
eggplant
into
1-inch
cubes;
cook in boiling, salted water 8 minutes; drain. Add egg, milk, butter, onion and
dry bread crumbs.
Put into greased, 1 quart baking dish.
Top
with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix chopped nuts and coconut.
Spread on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Spread over coconut and pecans.
Do not bake yet.
Mix cream cheese with butter and powdered sugar.
Spoon on top of cake batter (do not spread).
When done the top will look like earthquake cracks.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook rice, cook broccoli and melt cheese.
Mix all together and add mushroom soup.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except egg whites.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: celery-apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add candies to boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Add enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add to dissolved gelatin.
Cool until partly set, then add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold and chill until set. Unmold on lettuce and serve with mayonnaise.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll in balls. Put in freezer and let harden. Remove few at a time.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Stick toothpick in balls.
Dip in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: happy life
directions: Mix well, add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Flavor with love and kind service.
Fold in 4 large cups of prayer and faith. Pour into your daily life, bake well with heat of human kindness. Serve it with a smile and it will satisfy the hunger of many souls.

title: broccoli-grape salad
directions: Cut up the first 3 ingredients.
Mix mayo, vinegar and sweetener.
Mix with the first 3 ingredients.
Top with sunflower seeds.
Let mellow for a few hours before serving.

title: easy sherbet
directions: Mix in bowl. Put in freezer for 4 hours. Beat quick with beater. Return to freezer for 1 hour.

title: six-can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef with horseradish sauce
directions: Brown meat in 4 tablespoons butter; remove to casserole.
Brown onions in remaining butter; add to casserole along with curry powder, ginger, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and wine.
Bake covered in slow oven (300°) about 3 hours or until meat is tender. Just before serving, combine sour cream and horseradish; stir into meat along with parsley.
Serve on rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Mix in egg and flavorings.
Measure flour and blend dry ingredients; stir in.
Refrigerate at least 2 or 3 hours.

title: coconut bombs-bombs
directions: Melt oleo in double boiler.
Add coconut, the nuts, cherries, powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.
Shape into balls and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Dip in chocolate (melted) with paraffin.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into thick slices, cut slices into strips. Brush with salad dressing. Place on cookie sheet, season to taste. Bake 375 degrees for 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: broccoli-lima casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and lima beans following package directions. Drain and mix together gently.
Place in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Layer mushroom soup, sour cream, onion soup mix and water chestnuts on top of vegetables.
Melt oleo and mix with Rice Krispies.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap tortillas in foil; heat in oven for 10 minutes, until softened.

title: keebler no-bake brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk and chocolate chips; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Mix in graham crackers and nuts on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm; cut into squares.

title: jason's favorite broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, bacon and raisins.
Set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mix.
Stir until broccoli is covered with mayonnaise mix; chill. Enjoy.
(Can be made ahead.)

title: hot crock-pot dip
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Melt Velveeta and Cheddar cheese.
Add picante sauce, soup and garlic powder. Add meats and onion.
Keep hot and serve in crock-pot.

title: hawaiian sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Drain pineapple (save syrup) and saute in butter, onion, green pepper and pineapple.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, catsup and brown sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Add pork and beans and stir gently to mix.
Bake 45 minutes until it thickens.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook onion and peppers in butter until tender. Add flour and mix. Add remaining ingredients and put in a large greased casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Add pineapple to remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
